1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:02,786
The most entertaining suspense
that predicts love.

2
00:00:02,786 --> 00:00:04,726
Love line prediction game, Heart Signal.

3
00:00:04,726 --> 00:00:08,496
Five people with sharp romance
radars have gathered.

4
00:00:08,496 --> 00:00:10,476
Good to see you.

5
00:00:11,436 --> 00:00:14,766
I thought it was the last episode
last week because everything ended.

6
00:00:14,766 --> 00:00:15,736
You're right.

7
00:00:15,736 --> 00:00:19,776
Wu Yeol and Yu Gyeong had
a private tea room date.

8
00:00:19,776 --> 00:00:22,056
It was dizzying. Absolutely dizzying.

9
00:00:22,056 --> 00:00:24,346
I feel at peace now.

10
00:00:24,346 --> 00:00:26,616
Things are finally settling down.

11
00:00:26,616 --> 00:00:28,686
Rather than holding hands,

12
00:00:28,686 --> 00:00:31,916
having shoulders touching is more exciting.

13
00:00:31,916 --> 00:00:33,076
So exciting.

14
00:00:33,076 --> 00:00:37,016
I thought they didn't know
how to eat on their own.

15
00:00:37,016 --> 00:00:39,586
They weren't even tasting
what they were eating.

16
00:00:39,586 --> 00:00:42,136
All they felt was their shoulders touching.

17
00:00:42,136 --> 00:00:44,306
They probably
don't remember the movie at all.

18
00:00:44,306 --> 00:00:49,196
I felt at peace as Wu Yeol and
Yu Gyeong's relationship advanced.

19
00:00:49,196 --> 00:00:52,466
But the overall love lines
got even more tangled.

20
00:00:52,466 --> 00:00:55,296
None of them is in their right mind.

21
00:00:55,296 --> 00:00:57,526
- No one's feelings are resolved.
- Right, right.

22
00:00:57,526 --> 00:01:00,426
To Min Ju, Seong Min said,

23
00:01:00,426 --> 00:01:03,536
"Thanks for liking me,
but I'll try pursuing her again."

24
00:01:03,536 --> 00:01:06,066
That was implied.

25
00:01:06,066 --> 00:01:10,406
I'm staying quiet because Min Ju likes him,

26
00:01:10,406 --> 00:01:14,356
but I'm not so thrilled
about Seong Min, either.

27
00:01:14,356 --> 00:01:17,146
And there was the exciting nickname date.

28
00:01:17,146 --> 00:01:19,986
Pure Rabbit asked Salt Bread out.

29
00:01:19,986 --> 00:01:23,196
It ended cleanly without hard feelings.

30
00:01:23,196 --> 00:01:24,016
Right.

31
00:01:24,016 --> 00:01:26,976
Of all the people I've seen,

32
00:01:26,976 --> 00:01:30,146
she's the most economical with her words.

33
00:01:30,146 --> 00:01:33,536
It feels more confusing to talk around it.

34
00:01:33,536 --> 00:01:34,976
I'll just say it.

35
00:01:34,976 --> 00:01:38,836
She didn't say
an unnecessary word or comment.

36
00:01:38,836 --> 00:01:40,816
It was so great.

37
00:01:40,816 --> 00:01:43,536
She struggled a lot more than it seemed.

38
00:01:43,536 --> 00:01:47,776
But she still can have
such a great conversation.

39
00:01:47,776 --> 00:01:51,126
They reminded us why we fell for her

40
00:01:51,126 --> 00:01:54,466
when we first got to know her.

41
00:01:54,466 --> 00:01:56,476
This is so fun.

42
00:01:56,476 --> 00:01:58,446
It really is so fun.

43
00:01:58,446 --> 00:02:02,416
[A morning with warm sunshine]

44
00:02:02,416 --> 00:02:06,626
[Everyone is starting their day]

45
00:02:06,626 --> 00:02:08,226
[Rolling]

46
00:02:10,056 --> 00:02:11,706
[Rolling]

47
00:02:13,536 --> 00:02:16,596
[Seong Min is heading to the first floor]

48
00:02:18,516 --> 00:02:21,636
Gosh. You spooked me.

49
00:02:21,636 --> 00:02:22,986
- Taking coffee to work?
- Yes.

50
00:02:22,986 --> 00:02:24,876
Seong Min agreed to drive her.

51
00:02:25,496 --> 00:02:27,866
I heard Yu Gyeong is going today, too.

52
00:02:27,866 --> 00:02:29,486
- Where?
- To school.

53
00:02:29,486 --> 00:02:30,686
Someone is driving her.

54
00:02:30,686 --> 00:02:31,886
Who is?

55
00:02:32,526 --> 00:02:33,796
Wu Yeol.

56
00:02:36,566 --> 00:02:38,266
This is waking me up.

57
00:02:38,266 --> 00:02:40,476
- It's fascinating.
- I know.

58
00:02:42,076 --> 00:02:44,016
Didn't you chat before
you went to bed last night?

59
00:02:44,016 --> 00:02:45,786
I kept hearing your voice.

60
00:02:45,786 --> 00:02:48,756
I did. It was So Yun and the four boys.

61
00:02:49,786 --> 00:02:55,376
Do you think your feelings could
change in the next few days?

62
00:02:55,376 --> 00:03:00,266
I haven't been able to make a decision.

63
00:03:01,036 --> 00:03:04,586
It could easily change. Definitely.
And so what if it doesn't.

64
00:03:05,436 --> 00:03:08,226
Just do as you feel like.

65
00:03:08,226 --> 00:03:09,316
Right.

66
00:03:09,316 --> 00:03:11,836
Which matters more,
the first or the last 10 days?

67
00:03:11,836 --> 00:03:14,016
- Of course, the last.
- It's all about the last push.

68
00:03:14,016 --> 00:03:15,836
I know how to push at the end.

69
00:03:15,836 --> 00:03:18,816
- I wait and then...
- Some people have slow starts.

70
00:03:18,816 --> 00:03:20,826
I start really slowly.

71
00:03:22,056 --> 00:03:25,366
[You, too? Me, too]

72
00:03:26,036 --> 00:03:28,056
[Heart sign]

73
00:03:28,056 --> 00:03:29,376
So timid.

74
00:03:29,376 --> 00:03:32,006
- Those are scissors.
- I love it.

75
00:03:32,676 --> 00:03:34,166
How do I be honest?

76
00:03:34,166 --> 00:03:38,056
I was trying to be as honest as possible.

77
00:03:39,146 --> 00:03:41,996
[Last night, around the same time]

78
00:03:42,866 --> 00:03:44,426
You get many chances.

79
00:03:44,426 --> 00:03:47,866
- You need to create chances.
- Things could always change.

80
00:03:47,866 --> 00:03:49,086
And it's not bad to change your mind.

81
00:03:49,086 --> 00:03:51,436
It's natural to change your mind later.

82
00:03:51,436 --> 00:03:53,746
She's listening to everything.

83
00:03:53,746 --> 00:03:55,966
[She was listening to their
conversation in the room]

84
00:03:55,966 --> 00:03:59,156
Because you are going to work early,

85
00:04:00,076 --> 00:04:02,846
I was going to make you something tasty.

86
00:04:03,796 --> 00:04:08,036
I know every minute counts.

87
00:04:09,036 --> 00:04:13,336
I understand. I slept until the last minute.

88
00:04:15,226 --> 00:04:18,176
I should wrap it
so you can eat it on the way.

89
00:04:18,876 --> 00:04:21,966
- Wrap it?
- You have to try my French toast.

90
00:04:21,966 --> 00:04:24,066
- Right. I haven't tried it.
- Cute.

91
00:04:24,066 --> 00:04:25,176
I haven't tried it yet.

92
00:04:25,176 --> 00:04:26,986
It's really tasty.

93
00:04:27,986 --> 00:04:29,496
Looks good.

94
00:04:29,496 --> 00:04:33,966
I tend to brake suddenly
when I feel so happy.

95
00:04:33,966 --> 00:04:38,376
When I'm so happy, I fear that it will end.

96
00:04:38,376 --> 00:04:40,136
That's understandable.

97
00:04:42,796 --> 00:04:46,766
You must be happy at Signal House, then.

98
00:04:46,766 --> 00:04:49,606
Yes, I'm happy. I'm very happy.

99
00:04:49,606 --> 00:04:52,066
I'm afraid because I'm so happy.

100
00:04:52,066 --> 00:04:55,086
- Because it can't last forever.
- Right.

101
00:04:55,086 --> 00:05:00,526
I decided not to be upset
about that in advance.

102
00:05:00,526 --> 00:05:04,426
Really? I'm more excited about
what would happen after this.

103
00:05:04,426 --> 00:05:07,926
Remember the song we listened
to while we were biking?

104
00:05:07,926 --> 00:05:11,056
We listen to the Black Skirts' "Hollywood."

105
00:05:11,056 --> 00:05:13,896
- That was so romantic.
- I loved that so much.

106
00:05:13,896 --> 00:05:17,486
I've been listening to that
on repeat at work.

107
00:05:17,486 --> 00:05:20,856
That memory keeps me going at work.

108
00:05:21,506 --> 00:05:24,746
I'm like, "I'll go biking with Oppa again."

109
00:05:25,466 --> 00:05:27,536
You remember that song, too.

110
00:05:27,536 --> 00:05:30,506
Why is he getting her excited?

111
00:05:30,506 --> 00:05:33,756
It's always in the queue.

112
00:05:33,756 --> 00:05:36,756
Those are the only two songs I listen to.

113
00:05:38,506 --> 00:05:40,396
[Smiling]

114
00:05:40,396 --> 00:05:41,886
Hi.

115
00:05:44,586 --> 00:05:47,416
[They are having a simple breakfast together]

116
00:05:47,416 --> 00:05:49,216
[Yogurt wrapper]

117
00:05:53,796 --> 00:05:55,616
Do you always lick that?

118
00:05:56,436 --> 00:05:58,146
I felt like trying it.

119
00:06:00,776 --> 00:06:03,516
- How much do you want?
- One more scoop.

120
00:06:06,066 --> 00:06:10,396
I can't remember when,
but while I was asleep,

121
00:06:10,396 --> 00:06:12,856
my leg fell asleep.

122
00:06:12,856 --> 00:06:13,856
Mine, too.

123
00:06:13,856 --> 00:06:17,006
- Really? On your calf?
- Yes, so...

124
00:06:17,006 --> 00:06:19,136
I was screaming silently.

125
00:06:19,136 --> 00:06:23,276
Really? I screamed out loud.

126
00:06:23,276 --> 00:06:26,216
I must have moaned a lot.

127
00:06:26,216 --> 00:06:28,436
Min Ju gave me a massage.

128
00:06:28,436 --> 00:06:31,156
- Really?
- She came running upstairs.

129
00:06:31,156 --> 00:06:33,106
I wonder when that was.

130
00:06:33,106 --> 00:06:35,206
My leg fell asleep, too.

131
00:06:35,206 --> 00:06:37,826
- It still feels tight.
- I wonder why it fell asleep.

132
00:06:37,826 --> 00:06:40,076
It happens when you put
too much pressure on it.

133
00:06:40,076 --> 00:06:42,676
I know. I didn't know what to do.

134
00:06:46,666 --> 00:06:48,146
[Staring]

135
00:06:48,146 --> 00:06:49,946
But in the morning...

136
00:06:51,086 --> 00:06:54,636
you look the same as usual.

137
00:06:54,636 --> 00:06:57,836
- He's smitten.
- It's as puffy as it gets.

138
00:06:58,696 --> 00:07:00,746
It must be puffy. It has to be.

139
00:07:01,506 --> 00:07:04,946
I tend to cover it up with makeup.

140
00:07:06,326 --> 00:07:08,496
Can you cover up the puffiness?

141
00:07:10,296 --> 00:07:11,996
Finished.

142
00:07:15,006 --> 00:07:16,606
Cleared.

143
00:07:17,726 --> 00:07:20,456
It looks so moody.

144
00:07:20,456 --> 00:07:22,096
Let me see.

145
00:07:22,986 --> 00:07:25,466
It's nice. You're good.

146
00:07:26,646 --> 00:07:28,436
You're definitely an MZ.

147
00:07:29,886 --> 00:07:33,696
I'd better start getting ready now.

148
00:07:33,696 --> 00:07:35,186
We should go.

149
00:07:37,856 --> 00:07:39,236
Cheers.

150
00:07:39,936 --> 00:07:43,556
- What are you doing?
- They seem like newlyweds.

151
00:07:45,436 --> 00:07:48,446
When we go on another date,

152
00:07:49,756 --> 00:07:52,246
I'm curious about your spots.

153
00:07:52,946 --> 00:07:55,046
My spots?

154
00:07:55,046 --> 00:07:56,676
What could they be?

155
00:07:56,676 --> 00:07:59,366
- So cute.
- She can't hide her excitement.

156
00:08:00,196 --> 00:08:01,976
Your usual spots.

157
00:08:02,586 --> 00:08:06,596
- Anguk?
- I should invite you to my house.

158
00:08:06,596 --> 00:08:09,266
"I invite you to my house."

159
00:08:11,296 --> 00:08:13,116
How's my effort?

160
00:08:13,116 --> 00:08:14,836
Thank you.

161
00:08:21,826 --> 00:08:24,516
Will we get another chance to go on a date?

162
00:08:26,916 --> 00:08:29,066
[Yawning]

163
00:08:30,656 --> 00:08:32,276
How could you?

164
00:08:34,926 --> 00:08:36,556
A date? We probably will.

165
00:08:36,556 --> 00:08:39,086
We'll probably get another chance.

166
00:08:39,086 --> 00:08:41,346
Yes, probably.

167
00:08:44,666 --> 00:08:48,486
We have weekends.
We'll get the last weekend, too.

168
00:08:50,766 --> 00:08:53,626
[Yawning together]

169
00:08:55,026 --> 00:08:55,926
[Yawning together again]

170
00:08:55,926 --> 00:08:57,946
This means they are meant to be.

171
00:08:59,206 --> 00:09:01,996
I won't ask you for a ride anymore.

172
00:09:03,296 --> 00:09:05,206
No, ask me.

173
00:09:05,206 --> 00:09:07,586
Ask me for a ride. Where do you want to go?

174
00:09:07,586 --> 00:09:12,656
I hope I see people
when I wake up from a nap.

175
00:09:12,656 --> 00:09:16,746
I woke up and saw finger marks on my face.

176
00:09:16,746 --> 00:09:19,096
- Because you slept like this?
- Because I slept like this.

177
00:09:19,836 --> 00:09:24,536
I might've had a drool mark here, too.

178
00:09:25,306 --> 00:09:26,936
[Noticed her hair is up]

179
00:09:26,936 --> 00:09:28,326
Why did you tie your hair?

180
00:09:28,326 --> 00:09:33,506
It takes me two and a half hours
to style it in the morning.

181
00:09:33,506 --> 00:09:36,936
- Your hair.
- Yes, I'm really bad at it.

182
00:09:36,936 --> 00:09:38,696
- Two and a half hours?
- Yes.

183
00:09:38,696 --> 00:09:41,646
I look like a shaggy dog without it.

184
00:09:42,326 --> 00:09:45,236
- That has its own charm.
- Shaggy dog charm?

185
00:09:45,236 --> 00:09:50,226
You wouldn't have texted me
if I looked like a shaggy dog.

186
00:09:50,226 --> 00:09:52,216
This ended up taking longer.

187
00:09:52,846 --> 00:09:55,126
- I'm glad it did.
- Why?

188
00:09:55,896 --> 00:09:57,616
[Glancing]

189
00:09:59,166 --> 00:10:00,906
"Why?"

190
00:10:00,906 --> 00:10:03,566
You won't tell me why?

191
00:10:04,856 --> 00:10:07,886
I'll pretend
I accidentally went the wrong way.

192
00:10:08,516 --> 00:10:11,166
I'll get us 15 more minutes.

193
00:10:11,816 --> 00:10:15,226
Why did you suddenly give me
the throat candy yesterday?

194
00:10:15,226 --> 00:10:17,376
I thought you must have finished it.

195
00:10:17,376 --> 00:10:19,996
[Last night]

196
00:10:24,766 --> 00:10:26,016
Daebak.

197
00:10:26,656 --> 00:10:28,886
[Sneaking in a throat candy]

198
00:10:28,886 --> 00:10:30,406
Thank you.

199
00:10:32,626 --> 00:10:33,986
[Glancing]

200
00:10:36,136 --> 00:10:40,016
- They're both cute.
- I finished it that day.

201
00:10:40,016 --> 00:10:43,786
- I gave you a refill.
- Did you bring this much?

202
00:10:44,616 --> 00:10:46,566
Do you finish it in three days?

203
00:10:46,566 --> 00:10:47,796
A week?

204
00:10:47,796 --> 00:10:49,026
Yes.

205
00:10:49,026 --> 00:10:51,176
[Fiddling]

206
00:10:51,176 --> 00:10:52,886
Have a nice day.

207
00:10:52,886 --> 00:10:54,386
Bye.

208
00:11:01,436 --> 00:11:03,546
[Putting it away]

209
00:11:06,486 --> 00:11:12,596
[Everyone's starting the day
with different feelings]

210
00:11:12,596 --> 00:11:14,956
They're off to a good start today.

211
00:11:14,956 --> 00:11:16,856
So lovey-dovey.

212
00:11:17,586 --> 00:11:20,816
[The sunset on a weekday evening]

213
00:11:27,206 --> 00:11:31,466
[Jun Hyeon is home after work]

214
00:11:40,066 --> 00:11:45,146
[The house seems empty]

215
00:11:46,856 --> 00:11:48,826
No one's home.

216
00:11:56,126 --> 00:11:57,676
[Glancing]

217
00:12:03,166 --> 00:12:06,056
[My Dog, Yellow]

218
00:12:12,656 --> 00:12:14,216
Try it.

219
00:12:14,216 --> 00:12:15,716
Like this.

220
00:12:18,936 --> 00:12:22,086
[He had a fun time with Yu Gyeong]

221
00:12:22,086 --> 00:12:26,006
We need to see the end in a month.
How much longer...

222
00:12:26,006 --> 00:12:28,676
Do you think a month is long?

223
00:12:29,486 --> 00:12:31,656
- No.
- Right?

224
00:12:37,636 --> 00:12:43,336
Just like how you didn't
want me to feel pressured,

225
00:12:43,336 --> 00:12:46,956
you don't have to feel
pressured by what you said.

226
00:12:48,256 --> 00:12:50,336
About the fact that you told me.

227
00:12:57,336 --> 00:12:59,236
Yu Gyeong, are you okay?

228
00:12:59,236 --> 00:13:02,276
- Right now...
- Are you going to have ramen?

229
00:13:03,466 --> 00:13:06,686
Have some. Should I make you some?

230
00:13:06,686 --> 00:13:08,286
[Yu Gyeong seemed lost in thought]

231
00:13:11,856 --> 00:13:13,286
Are they cooking something?

232
00:13:13,286 --> 00:13:16,806
I think they're taking out food waste.

233
00:13:18,476 --> 00:13:21,336
- You are wearing soft pants.
- Yeah.

234
00:13:21,336 --> 00:13:23,076
They're warm.

235
00:13:28,126 --> 00:13:29,816
What are you doing tomorrow?

236
00:13:31,896 --> 00:13:35,066
- Do you have plans?
- He wants to ask her how she feels.

237
00:13:35,066 --> 00:13:38,736
Tomorrow? I might go out.

238
00:13:38,736 --> 00:13:40,316
Do you have a plan?

239
00:13:42,336 --> 00:13:44,636
Did someone approach you first?

240
00:13:44,636 --> 00:13:46,096
Jun Hyeon is coming on strongly.

241
00:13:46,096 --> 00:13:48,226
I think I might go out.

242
00:13:48,226 --> 00:13:50,706
You could have a plan, you mean?

243
00:13:51,786 --> 00:13:54,516
- Did you bring in your stuff?
- No.

244
00:13:54,516 --> 00:13:56,716
I haven't had a chance.

245
00:14:14,536 --> 00:14:17,866
[Jun Hyeon brings in Yu Gyeong's luggage]

246
00:14:17,866 --> 00:14:20,806
He approached her in his own way.

247
00:14:38,106 --> 00:14:41,446
- She happens to be home now.
- I know.

248
00:14:53,396 --> 00:14:54,576
Oh?

249
00:14:55,236 --> 00:14:57,096
- Hi.
- Look at that smile.

250
00:14:57,096 --> 00:15:00,076
- Hi, Oppa.
- Hi.

251
00:15:00,076 --> 00:15:01,926
Why is no one home?

252
00:15:01,926 --> 00:15:03,676
When did you get here?

253
00:15:03,676 --> 00:15:05,516
About...

254
00:15:05,516 --> 00:15:08,276
About 40 minutes ago?

255
00:15:08,276 --> 00:15:09,956
Is no one home?

256
00:15:09,956 --> 00:15:11,576
Is no one home?

257
00:15:11,576 --> 00:15:14,276
- I know. No one's home.
- Gosh.

258
00:15:15,786 --> 00:15:18,376
Two people left you a note.

259
00:15:19,256 --> 00:15:21,286
Is this Seo Won?

260
00:15:21,286 --> 00:15:23,156
[A note from someone]

261
00:15:25,426 --> 00:15:27,586
[I'll be late tonight. Good luck with dinner,
Seo Won and Yu Gyeong. - So Yun]

262
00:15:27,586 --> 00:15:29,816
Will you be relaxing today?

263
00:15:30,626 --> 00:15:32,466
Around four to six?

264
00:15:33,066 --> 00:15:36,996
- What about you?
- I might be home around the same time.

265
00:15:36,996 --> 00:15:39,056
I might get dinner outside.

266
00:15:39,056 --> 00:15:40,966
Really?

267
00:15:41,936 --> 00:15:43,406
Want me to pick up something?

268
00:15:43,406 --> 00:15:44,536
No.

269
00:15:45,456 --> 00:15:49,796
[It sounded like Wu Yeol had a plan]

270
00:15:52,996 --> 00:15:55,896
[So Yun said she'll be home late]

271
00:15:55,896 --> 00:15:57,756
[Buzzing]

272
00:16:01,926 --> 00:16:06,976
[Pure Rabbit wants to see Salt Bread]

273
00:16:09,756 --> 00:16:11,146
[Buzzing]

274
00:16:12,126 --> 00:16:16,636
[Dried Sweet Potato wants to see Salt Bread]

275
00:16:17,146 --> 00:16:19,796
[She kept hearing his phone buzzing]

276
00:16:22,516 --> 00:16:25,316
You're so quiet today.

277
00:16:25,316 --> 00:16:28,166
We talked a lot before you came home.

278
00:16:28,166 --> 00:16:30,766
We all got quiet as soon as you came home.

279
00:16:34,556 --> 00:16:37,646
How late are they going to be?

280
00:16:38,896 --> 00:16:40,186
Are they doing something?

281
00:16:40,186 --> 00:16:42,186
I hate you all.

282
00:16:42,186 --> 00:16:43,836
Hate you.

283
00:16:43,836 --> 00:16:47,076
- I told them to come home early.
- So cute.

284
00:16:47,076 --> 00:16:49,036
How disappointing.

285
00:16:49,036 --> 00:16:52,836
What would you like?
Are you craving something?

286
00:16:52,836 --> 00:16:55,246
- Tuna...
- Do we have tuna?

287
00:16:55,246 --> 00:16:58,266
I think we have some...

288
00:16:59,656 --> 00:17:03,886
- We have nabe and tteokbokki.
- Nabe?

289
00:17:03,886 --> 00:17:06,126
- How about tteokbokki?
- Would you like that?

290
00:17:06,126 --> 00:17:07,776
- How about tteokbokki?
- You don't mind?

291
00:17:07,776 --> 00:17:09,916
I would love some.

292
00:17:09,916 --> 00:17:12,946
- Brisket tteokbokki?
- Brisket tteokbokki?

293
00:17:12,946 --> 00:17:13,666
Sounds good.

294
00:17:13,666 --> 00:17:17,796
[Today's dinner is brisket tteokbokki]

295
00:17:19,256 --> 00:17:21,636
This will be so good.

296
00:17:23,996 --> 00:17:26,206
[Three nights ago]

297
00:17:26,206 --> 00:17:30,146
[Yu Gyeong came home early that day as usual]

298
00:17:32,686 --> 00:17:34,326
[Bumped into each other that day, too]

299
00:17:34,326 --> 00:17:37,426
- Dinner... Should we make dinner?
- We should.

300
00:17:37,426 --> 00:17:39,136
Let's make dinner.

301
00:17:39,136 --> 00:17:41,926
I'll be cooking for the first time.

302
00:17:41,926 --> 00:17:45,426
- How's fried rice and mapo tofu?
- I'd be grateful.

303
00:17:47,276 --> 00:17:51,226
It's written there. He must've
chosen from her list.

304
00:17:51,226 --> 00:17:53,986
I don't think we have tofu.

305
00:17:53,986 --> 00:17:56,106
Should I go get some? Should I?

306
00:17:56,106 --> 00:17:58,136
This should be enough rice, right?

307
00:17:58,756 --> 00:18:01,686
- It doesn't look like it's enough.
- But...

308
00:18:02,816 --> 00:18:05,596
[But Min Ju came home]

309
00:18:05,596 --> 00:18:07,126
Did you have a good day?

310
00:18:07,126 --> 00:18:09,416
- Of course, I did.
- Are you okay?

311
00:18:09,416 --> 00:18:11,156
- Hi.
- What's this?

312
00:18:11,156 --> 00:18:13,946
- So Yun.
- What? Did you go grocery shopping?

313
00:18:13,946 --> 00:18:16,376
Hi.

314
00:18:16,376 --> 00:18:19,036
I got my hair done today.

315
00:18:19,036 --> 00:18:20,536
He's signaling her.

316
00:18:20,536 --> 00:18:22,756
When did you get it done?

317
00:18:28,746 --> 00:18:32,826
[It's the same situation all over again]

318
00:18:32,826 --> 00:18:34,966
We should thaw the fish cake.

319
00:18:36,146 --> 00:18:38,736
- It says to use a large pot.
- A large one?

320
00:18:38,736 --> 00:18:41,096
- Isn't this big enough?
- It is.

321
00:18:41,096 --> 00:18:42,936
No, it's not.

322
00:18:42,936 --> 00:18:46,336
- I mean...
- We should use this.

323
00:18:48,936 --> 00:18:51,236
[Reading the instructions thoroughly]

324
00:18:51,236 --> 00:18:53,276
Slicing the fish cake thinly is...

325
00:18:53,276 --> 00:18:55,956
- The first step?
- The important part.

326
00:18:55,956 --> 00:18:59,576
- They say the thinner, the tastier.
- Really?

327
00:19:00,856 --> 00:19:02,966
We're in trouble.
It says to use the entire bag.

328
00:19:02,966 --> 00:19:04,766
We're not in trouble.

329
00:19:04,766 --> 00:19:08,236
We only looked at the pictures, not the text.

330
00:19:09,496 --> 00:19:10,706
Hold on.

331
00:19:10,706 --> 00:19:12,306
[Left behind]

332
00:19:15,056 --> 00:19:17,466
- I'll do this.
- What are you doing?

333
00:19:17,466 --> 00:19:20,166
No? I really shouldn't?

334
00:19:20,166 --> 00:19:22,556
It says to add 250 ml.

335
00:19:22,556 --> 00:19:23,526
Why...

336
00:19:25,756 --> 00:19:29,496
We can prepare the rest now.

337
00:19:31,946 --> 00:19:33,666
This will be tasty.

338
00:19:35,676 --> 00:19:38,626
- It looks so good.
- Her cooking improved living here.

339
00:19:38,626 --> 00:19:41,286
Will there be enough food, Oppa?

340
00:19:41,286 --> 00:19:43,506
No, I'll eat more later.

341
00:19:43,506 --> 00:19:45,286
I'll probably eat more at night.

342
00:19:45,286 --> 00:19:48,046
[A simple dinner]

343
00:19:49,026 --> 00:19:51,456
It's so good with the brisket.

344
00:19:56,096 --> 00:19:58,616
- Mm!
- Mm!

345
00:19:59,516 --> 00:20:01,136
It's good.

346
00:20:04,666 --> 00:20:05,926
[It's even tastier
because they cooked together]

347
00:20:05,926 --> 00:20:07,866
He keeps smiling.

348
00:20:07,866 --> 00:20:09,556
If you can't believe me...

349
00:20:09,556 --> 00:20:11,206
It's a hunch.

350
00:20:14,736 --> 00:20:16,326
[Yu Gyeong is writing a note]

351
00:20:19,906 --> 00:20:21,356
She's cute.

352
00:20:21,356 --> 00:20:22,886
[I hate you all]

353
00:20:22,886 --> 00:20:24,676
[After cleaning up]

354
00:20:25,326 --> 00:20:26,146
[Click]

355
00:20:27,326 --> 00:20:29,866
[Setting things up properly]

356
00:20:30,536 --> 00:20:38,736
[They're each taking a break and relaxing]

357
00:20:43,416 --> 00:20:45,466
Should we do something?

358
00:20:46,086 --> 00:20:48,146
- Do you want a gift?
- A gift?

359
00:20:48,146 --> 00:20:50,266
- A gift?
- Oh, my gosh.

360
00:20:50,266 --> 00:20:52,226
I didn't get it just for you.

361
00:20:52,226 --> 00:20:53,916
[Bags full of gifts]

362
00:20:53,916 --> 00:20:56,866
They get it for everyone when they're
too shy to give it to one person.

363
00:20:56,866 --> 00:20:58,956
Wow, what is it? Daebak.

364
00:20:58,956 --> 00:21:01,276
It's for Valentine's Day.

365
00:21:01,276 --> 00:21:04,326
- So, I got four.
- Of course, you did.

366
00:21:04,326 --> 00:21:06,886
Daebak, it's so pretty. What is it?

367
00:21:06,886 --> 00:21:10,986
Wow. Give it to everyone privately.

368
00:21:10,986 --> 00:21:13,746
Can I open it? I think it will be so pretty.

369
00:21:13,746 --> 00:21:16,786
Wow, this is pretty, too.

370
00:21:20,886 --> 00:21:22,816
He's happy. He's happy.

371
00:21:22,816 --> 00:21:24,626
[So happy]

372
00:21:25,146 --> 00:21:27,256
I should be careful.

373
00:21:27,256 --> 00:21:32,326
Wow, it looks so fancy.

374
00:21:32,326 --> 00:21:34,506
I had no idea.

375
00:21:34,506 --> 00:21:36,986
Thank you so much.

376
00:21:36,986 --> 00:21:38,936
You're the best. Looks tasty.

377
00:21:38,936 --> 00:21:41,196
I'm sure only hers has almonds in it.

378
00:21:41,196 --> 00:21:43,756
I know it's two days away, but...

379
00:21:43,756 --> 00:21:49,636
I think I could use this as a hair tie.

380
00:21:51,906 --> 00:21:54,496
There's nothing to do at home.

381
00:21:54,496 --> 00:21:57,066
I'm bored now.

382
00:21:57,066 --> 00:21:59,376
You should've watched something.

383
00:22:00,056 --> 00:22:02,706
I'll eat these secretly.

384
00:22:03,546 --> 00:22:07,296
I'll pretend like I'm not
giving it to anyone else.

385
00:22:14,396 --> 00:22:16,836
[Setting up]

386
00:22:17,936 --> 00:22:20,366
Who do you think chose the
comic book? Can you guess?

387
00:22:20,366 --> 00:22:22,446
- I think I know.
- Who?

388
00:22:22,446 --> 00:22:24,876
I won't show any reaction.

389
00:22:24,876 --> 00:22:26,156
What are you talking about?

390
00:22:26,156 --> 00:22:28,726
- I won't say anything.
- What does that have to do with it?

391
00:22:28,726 --> 00:22:31,316
I'm curious if women could tell.

392
00:22:31,316 --> 00:22:32,626
No, I won't tell you.

393
00:22:32,626 --> 00:22:34,526
Do comic books remind you of someone?

394
00:22:34,526 --> 00:22:39,146
I talked a lot about comic books
with someone.

395
00:22:40,506 --> 00:22:42,466
[Thinking]

396
00:22:42,466 --> 00:22:43,956
It's tasty.

397
00:22:44,606 --> 00:22:47,386
I think I guessed all the men's correctly.

398
00:22:47,386 --> 00:22:49,036
How did you guess men's?

399
00:22:49,036 --> 00:22:50,526
I just had a feeling.

400
00:22:50,526 --> 00:22:53,786
The nickname resembles the person.

401
00:22:53,786 --> 00:22:56,096
I think only one resembles someone.

402
00:22:56,096 --> 00:22:58,336
Which one? The camel?

403
00:22:58,336 --> 00:23:03,716
You're just guessing?
He does look like a camel.

404
00:23:03,716 --> 00:23:06,216
Only one person does.

405
00:23:10,406 --> 00:23:13,896
What's with Yellow? Do they resemble a dog?

406
00:23:13,896 --> 00:23:16,276
It's just a dog's name.

407
00:23:17,996 --> 00:23:21,926
- I'm revealing too much now.
- I mean...

408
00:23:26,276 --> 00:23:29,366
We went to Japan a week ago already.

409
00:23:29,366 --> 00:23:30,956
Really?

410
00:23:32,686 --> 00:23:34,356
It's been a week already?

411
00:23:34,356 --> 00:23:36,256
Gosh, you're right.

412
00:23:41,276 --> 00:23:44,616
- Did you say you like summer over winter?
- Yes.

413
00:23:45,836 --> 00:23:48,326
Summer vs. winter.

414
00:23:48,326 --> 00:23:49,436
Summer.

415
00:23:49,436 --> 00:23:51,886
- I'm the same.
- Really?

416
00:23:51,886 --> 00:23:57,416
Did you... Did you hate the cold?

417
00:23:57,416 --> 00:24:00,036
- What did you say?
- We talked about this before.

418
00:24:00,036 --> 00:24:02,786
- I know.
- Do you hate the cold?

419
00:24:02,786 --> 00:24:06,096
- Which is it? Speak clearly.
- No, no, no...

420
00:24:07,996 --> 00:24:10,036
- You hate catching a cold.
- Right, I do.

421
00:24:10,036 --> 00:24:12,836
You hate the cold because
you are afraid of catching a cold.

422
00:24:12,836 --> 00:24:14,746
Right. That was it.

423
00:24:18,686 --> 00:24:20,186
[Dimple]

424
00:24:20,186 --> 00:24:22,266
I hate the cold.

425
00:24:22,266 --> 00:24:25,806
- Right. Should we watch that?
- Watch what?

426
00:24:25,806 --> 00:24:28,516
- A balance game video?
- I love stuff like that.

427
00:24:28,516 --> 00:24:30,536
- Balance game.
- Right.

428
00:24:30,536 --> 00:24:33,406
2.9 million views. Is that good enough?

429
00:24:33,406 --> 00:24:37,546
[Starting the balance game]

430
00:24:37,546 --> 00:24:38,796
[Happy fake world vs. sad real world]

431
00:24:38,796 --> 00:24:40,356
- I choose A.
- I choose A.

432
00:24:40,356 --> 00:24:42,566
- A?
- Yes, A.

433
00:24:43,546 --> 00:24:45,156
Geez, this is hard. Hold on.

434
00:24:45,156 --> 00:24:46,836
A, A, A.

435
00:24:46,836 --> 00:24:48,816
You have to choose one. Hurry.

436
00:24:48,816 --> 00:24:50,856
You can't pause. Hurry.

437
00:24:50,856 --> 00:24:54,486
- No, please pause it.
- You have to choose in 5 seconds.

438
00:24:54,486 --> 00:24:56,486
But fake is sad.

439
00:24:56,486 --> 00:24:58,286
But the sad world might be too hard.

440
00:24:58,286 --> 00:24:59,776
Life is supposed to be sad.

441
00:24:59,776 --> 00:25:01,966
You are right. Life is painful.

442
00:25:01,966 --> 00:25:05,606
You could be grateful for small things.

443
00:25:05,606 --> 00:25:07,106
It's B, then.

444
00:25:07,106 --> 00:25:10,526
- I convinced you.
- I've been convinced.

445
00:25:10,526 --> 00:25:11,956
He's acting like he was.

446
00:25:11,956 --> 00:25:14,826
A. Summer.

447
00:25:16,476 --> 00:25:18,026
- Dog.
- Dog.

448
00:25:18,026 --> 00:25:20,216
Hold on. Hold on.

449
00:25:20,216 --> 00:25:21,986
- This is hard.
- I'm torn.

450
00:25:21,986 --> 00:25:23,966
I change my mind about this every year.

451
00:25:23,966 --> 00:25:25,276
I like fried chicken these days.

452
00:25:25,276 --> 00:25:28,126
I used to be on Team Pizza, too.

453
00:25:28,126 --> 00:25:29,476
But fried chicken is good.

454
00:25:29,476 --> 00:25:31,296
What kind of pizza do you like?

455
00:25:31,296 --> 00:25:34,096
I eat anything. I like Hawaiian, too.

456
00:25:34,096 --> 00:25:36,776
I like how the evening feels more.

457
00:25:36,776 --> 00:25:39,396
- I don't want to experience mourning.
- Evenings are more fun.

458
00:25:39,396 --> 00:25:41,866
- A lot of fun things happen.
- Right.

459
00:25:41,866 --> 00:25:43,776
A clear day.

460
00:25:43,776 --> 00:25:45,926
- I hate carrying the umbrella.
- Me, too.

461
00:25:45,926 --> 00:25:47,716
I just got rained on instead.

462
00:25:47,716 --> 00:25:50,656
Me, too. I don't carry an umbrella.

463
00:25:50,656 --> 00:25:52,946
You don't use an umbrella?

464
00:25:52,946 --> 00:25:54,856
I actually don't.

465
00:25:54,856 --> 00:25:57,186
Rest, obviously. Are they crazy?

466
00:25:57,186 --> 00:25:58,346
Look at this.

467
00:25:58,346 --> 00:26:00,866
Look at that pose.

468
00:26:00,866 --> 00:26:04,476
- He's compatible with Yu Gyeong.
- This looks stressful.

469
00:26:04,476 --> 00:26:07,896
[Time is going by fast tonight]

470
00:26:07,896 --> 00:26:10,476
I think Jun Hyeon...

471
00:26:10,476 --> 00:26:15,236
is the closest to my ideal type
of all men here.

472
00:26:15,236 --> 00:26:18,456
I like someone simple and straightforward.

473
00:26:18,456 --> 00:26:22,386
I like how he expresses himself
without being too much.

474
00:26:22,386 --> 00:26:25,976
I think he adjusts himself
to Yu Gyeong a lot.

475
00:26:25,976 --> 00:26:29,166
He seems to have strong views,

476
00:26:29,166 --> 00:26:31,416
but he's not unreasonably stubborn.

477
00:26:31,416 --> 00:26:33,426
During the game,
he was like, "I think you're right."

478
00:26:33,426 --> 00:26:34,936
"I like it if you like it."

479
00:26:34,936 --> 00:26:39,336
And he's the kind of type
who isn't domineering.

480
00:26:39,336 --> 00:26:41,236
When you have a worry,

481
00:26:41,236 --> 00:26:45,356
you can't share it with
someone who approaches you.

482
00:26:45,356 --> 00:26:48,646
But when somebody is on your side quietly,

483
00:26:48,646 --> 00:26:53,386
you find it easier to talk
to them. He's like that.

484
00:26:53,386 --> 00:26:55,106
Right.

485
00:27:02,096 --> 00:27:03,806
Min Ju.

486
00:27:03,806 --> 00:27:07,796
[She's waiting for someone]

487
00:27:09,936 --> 00:27:13,506
- Could it be Jun Hyeon?
- Could be. To know him better.

488
00:27:13,506 --> 00:27:15,326
It could be Seong Min, too.

489
00:27:15,326 --> 00:27:19,396
[Will it be someone she is hoping for?]

490
00:27:20,036 --> 00:27:24,906
[Waiting for her date]

491
00:27:24,906 --> 00:27:28,086
[Easy way to start reading, start with Kyobo]

492
00:27:29,346 --> 00:27:33,986
[Reviewing her date's library]

493
00:27:34,506 --> 00:27:38,086
[Busy Hamster's library]

494
00:27:43,506 --> 00:27:44,466
[Pushing the like button]

495
00:27:50,966 --> 00:27:53,586
I want to look at the rest.

496
00:28:03,626 --> 00:28:07,106
[Today, they are having nickname dates]

497
00:28:07,786 --> 00:28:10,986
[Name the nickname
you are most curious about]

498
00:28:10,986 --> 00:28:11,856
[Busy Hamster]

499
00:28:11,856 --> 00:28:14,706
- Hamster.
- That's so Min Ju.

500
00:28:18,876 --> 00:28:20,596
[Turning around]

501
00:28:23,846 --> 00:28:25,106
[Busy Hamster was Seong Min]

502
00:28:25,106 --> 00:28:27,536
It was you.

503
00:28:27,536 --> 00:28:28,876
[Smiling]

504
00:28:28,876 --> 00:28:30,956
- Hi.
- It was Min Ju.

505
00:28:30,956 --> 00:28:34,556
She must have doubts
about Hamster being Seong Min.

506
00:28:34,556 --> 00:28:36,486
She still likes him.

507
00:28:36,486 --> 00:28:38,016
- What's the deal?
- Aren't you cold?

508
00:28:38,016 --> 00:28:39,166
No.

509
00:28:39,166 --> 00:28:41,526
Did you wait outside for a long time?

510
00:28:41,526 --> 00:28:43,446
I just got here.

511
00:28:46,386 --> 00:28:47,966
I need to stop smiling.

512
00:28:47,966 --> 00:28:49,306
Why? Why?

513
00:28:49,306 --> 00:28:51,786
- I'm so excited.
- I keep smiling, too.

514
00:28:51,786 --> 00:28:54,836
- I'm way too excited.
- Are you?

515
00:28:54,836 --> 00:28:58,076
This place feels so different right now.

516
00:28:58,076 --> 00:29:01,416
I know. Doesn't it feel like we're on a trip?

517
00:29:01,416 --> 00:29:03,366
- Is this it?
- Yes.

518
00:29:03,366 --> 00:29:05,626
- Let's go.
- Let's go.

519
00:29:07,796 --> 00:29:09,556
Look. Did you see that?

520
00:29:10,336 --> 00:29:12,536
- It's so cool.
- I love this place.

521
00:29:12,536 --> 00:29:13,746
[An exotic atmosphere]

522
00:29:13,746 --> 00:29:17,526
- It's so nice and warm in here.
- I know, it's so warm.

523
00:29:18,286 --> 00:29:21,056
Because it's cold outside,

524
00:29:21,056 --> 00:29:23,516
- should we get a mushroom soup?
- Sounds good.

525
00:29:24,456 --> 00:29:26,766
They have dark beer here, too.

526
00:29:26,766 --> 00:29:29,356
- I'll give it a try.
- You don't have to get it.

527
00:29:29,356 --> 00:29:33,566
I'll order one and take little sips.

528
00:29:34,396 --> 00:29:36,256
Thank you.

529
00:29:36,826 --> 00:29:39,876
- Daebak, what's this?
- It looks so good.

530
00:29:40,556 --> 00:29:42,706
I don't think I can wait.

531
00:29:42,706 --> 00:29:45,676
[Taking photos before the meal]

532
00:29:46,236 --> 00:29:49,246
It's so cute how they're
taking photos of each other.

533
00:29:49,246 --> 00:29:53,386
[They photographed each other in Japan]

534
00:29:54,396 --> 00:29:56,126
That one's nice.

535
00:29:56,736 --> 00:29:59,116
What's the deal?

536
00:29:59,116 --> 00:30:02,866
[They are photographing
each other again today]

537
00:30:05,956 --> 00:30:07,156
[Got the reaction he was waiting for]

538
00:30:07,156 --> 00:30:08,776
She makes that face when something's tasty.

539
00:30:08,776 --> 00:30:11,266
This is delicious. I'm not exaggerating.

540
00:30:11,266 --> 00:30:14,506
This is on another level. It really is.

541
00:30:14,506 --> 00:30:16,926
Seriously. Don't you agree?

542
00:30:16,926 --> 00:30:21,106
[Can't pass on a drink]

543
00:30:23,026 --> 00:30:25,396
I'm so glad you ordered this.

544
00:30:25,396 --> 00:30:27,046
- Is it good?
- Yes.

545
00:30:27,046 --> 00:30:28,736
Good thing we got it.

546
00:30:29,706 --> 00:30:32,416
- You drank a little bit last night.
- I did.

547
00:30:32,416 --> 00:30:33,776
You sipped on a glass or two.

548
00:30:33,776 --> 00:30:36,496
Yes, but I felt okay.

549
00:30:37,216 --> 00:30:40,226
- I'm getting better.
- So cute.

550
00:30:40,226 --> 00:30:42,236
It's nice to commute together.

551
00:30:42,236 --> 00:30:44,206
I know. We're eating together
after work, too.

552
00:30:44,206 --> 00:30:46,276
Yes, it's fun.

553
00:30:47,026 --> 00:30:49,736
How's your new job? You said it's fun.

554
00:30:49,736 --> 00:30:53,396
It is fun. Everyone is nice.

555
00:30:53,396 --> 00:30:56,546
I said I want to work on an ad myself.

556
00:30:56,546 --> 00:31:03,266
We worked on the strategy
to make the right kind of ad.

557
00:31:03,266 --> 00:31:05,276
So, I did that in the morning.

558
00:31:05,276 --> 00:31:10,716
I was asked to do monitoring today,
so I wrote a report.

559
00:31:10,716 --> 00:31:14,116
Fascinating.
I don't know anything about that.

560
00:31:14,116 --> 00:31:16,456
- Marketing.
- I only know what I know.

561
00:31:17,366 --> 00:31:20,876
Why are you Busy Hamster, by the way?

562
00:31:20,876 --> 00:31:23,296
I feel like I overworked myself.

563
00:31:23,296 --> 00:31:26,916
I'm always like, "Please work on this.
Please have a look at this.

564
00:31:26,916 --> 00:31:29,216
Please get this and this ready."

565
00:31:29,216 --> 00:31:33,016
They said I looked like
a busy hamster, apparently.

566
00:31:33,016 --> 00:31:37,296
And my life is so hectic, too.

567
00:31:38,026 --> 00:31:41,326
It's even cuter now that I know why.

568
00:31:41,326 --> 00:31:43,116
She can't find him cute.

569
00:31:43,116 --> 00:31:44,826
Your face got red.

570
00:31:44,826 --> 00:31:46,726
Did it? That's not good.

571
00:31:46,726 --> 00:31:48,766
Just a little. Just a little.

572
00:31:48,766 --> 00:31:51,066
- Are you okay?
- Oh, no. Am I getting redder?

573
00:31:51,066 --> 00:31:53,076
You aren't that red.

574
00:31:53,076 --> 00:31:56,446
The day Jun Hyeon joined us,

575
00:31:56,446 --> 00:31:59,596
- I was a bit surprised.
- Really?

576
00:31:59,596 --> 00:32:01,236
I was like, "Why is she so red?"

577
00:32:01,236 --> 00:32:03,246
[Giving her water]

578
00:32:05,216 --> 00:32:06,976
- I'm sad.
- Why?

579
00:32:06,976 --> 00:32:12,236
I'm the only one who turns red so easily.

580
00:32:12,236 --> 00:32:16,556
You drank about four glasses of water.

581
00:32:16,556 --> 00:32:18,326
Me? That's right.

582
00:32:19,336 --> 00:32:21,516
You turned so red.

583
00:32:21,516 --> 00:32:24,736
- Drink water.
- Okay. I wanted to drink it.

584
00:32:24,736 --> 00:32:28,616
[The moment she realized Seong Min was sweet]

585
00:32:29,316 --> 00:32:31,636
- You want me to drink this?
- Yes.

586
00:32:32,586 --> 00:32:34,676
- I don't think I can.
- Okay, I'll drink it.

587
00:32:34,676 --> 00:32:36,116
[He continues to be sweet]

588
00:32:36,856 --> 00:32:40,656
[Suddenly feeling grateful]

589
00:32:43,246 --> 00:32:45,846
You really love drinking, don't you?

590
00:32:45,846 --> 00:32:47,386
I think so.

591
00:32:47,386 --> 00:32:52,036
I've been drinking because
I feel stressed here, too.

592
00:32:52,036 --> 00:32:54,936
Everyone seems to have a lot on their mind.

593
00:32:55,936 --> 00:32:58,506
They seem to have a lot of worries, too.

594
00:32:58,506 --> 00:33:02,126
You seem to have a lot, too.

595
00:33:06,016 --> 00:33:07,906
Did it seem that way?

596
00:33:10,186 --> 00:33:13,946
I'm okay now. I used to be so stressed out.

597
00:33:14,956 --> 00:33:20,066
I think I was having a hard time in Japan.

598
00:33:21,026 --> 00:33:23,676
She's not as hung up.

599
00:33:23,676 --> 00:33:29,636
To be honest, I wondered
if I was sincere on my own.

600
00:33:29,636 --> 00:33:38,236
And I move on if I feel like
I'm going to get hurt.

601
00:33:38,236 --> 00:33:43,946
I think that was a way to protect myself.

602
00:33:43,946 --> 00:33:45,696
Right.

603
00:33:47,746 --> 00:33:49,506
But now,

604
00:33:53,686 --> 00:33:56,756
I decided to keep things simple.

605
00:33:56,756 --> 00:34:01,546
I decided to focus on myself rather
than guessing how other people feel.

606
00:34:01,546 --> 00:34:04,876
Deciding that freed me so much.

607
00:34:06,716 --> 00:34:09,396
So, I'm really happy right now.

608
00:34:09,396 --> 00:34:13,866
Like having tasty food and hanging
out with you right now.

609
00:34:14,636 --> 00:34:17,676
That's why I can eat
and sleep well these days.

610
00:34:17,676 --> 00:34:20,116
My new job is so fun, too.

611
00:34:25,336 --> 00:34:27,656
Seong Min has a lot on his mind.

612
00:34:30,446 --> 00:34:32,756
I started struggling since then.

613
00:34:32,756 --> 00:34:35,686
- That means...
- Since when?

614
00:34:35,686 --> 00:34:38,686
[Thinking]

615
00:34:43,026 --> 00:34:45,076
I think...

616
00:34:45,076 --> 00:34:49,526
- I like one person.
- Ever since he heard that?

617
00:34:54,006 --> 00:34:56,346
This is so nice.

618
00:34:56,346 --> 00:34:59,686
I wanted this moment to last forever.

619
00:34:59,686 --> 00:35:01,216
[That day had a big impact on him]

620
00:35:06,226 --> 00:35:07,786
You're still having a hard time?

621
00:35:07,786 --> 00:35:09,316
I...

622
00:35:10,026 --> 00:35:11,516
I'm still happy.

623
00:35:11,516 --> 00:35:16,566
I'm grateful to be able
to experience this at all.

624
00:35:17,526 --> 00:35:19,726
I like the situation I'm in, too.

625
00:35:19,726 --> 00:35:21,436
But that...

626
00:35:22,436 --> 00:35:24,446
I'm not sure.
I haven't reached a conclusion yet.

627
00:35:24,446 --> 00:35:26,316
We have 10 days left, too.

628
00:35:26,316 --> 00:35:28,296
- Yes, we have a lot of time.
- A lot of time.

629
00:35:28,296 --> 00:35:31,046
Ten days is longer than you think.

630
00:35:34,756 --> 00:35:37,136
I brought something.

631
00:35:37,136 --> 00:35:39,026
What is it?

632
00:35:39,026 --> 00:35:42,956
I actually knew it would be you.

633
00:35:42,956 --> 00:35:48,206
I kept thinking, "Hamster must be Seong Min."

634
00:35:48,206 --> 00:35:53,096
Because you seem stressed out lately,

635
00:35:53,096 --> 00:35:55,466
I got you a small gift.

636
00:35:56,796 --> 00:35:58,236
What is it?

637
00:35:58,896 --> 00:36:00,356
Ta-da.

638
00:36:01,016 --> 00:36:04,216
- Didn't you say you have plants?
- I do.

639
00:36:04,216 --> 00:36:07,076
I want you to look at this and cheer up.

640
00:36:07,076 --> 00:36:09,386
It has a note. Can I read it?

641
00:36:10,646 --> 00:36:11,986
[Embarrassed]

642
00:36:11,986 --> 00:36:15,426
- Gosh. Who else does this?
- This is...

643
00:36:17,986 --> 00:36:19,866
"I hope this becomes a breath of fresh air."

644
00:36:19,866 --> 00:36:22,106
Min Ju is so sincere.

645
00:36:22,106 --> 00:36:25,896
Its meaning is "A precious connection,"
apparently.

646
00:36:28,146 --> 00:36:31,406
- Are you moved?
- Thank you. This is so moving.

647
00:36:31,406 --> 00:36:33,476
What did I write?

648
00:36:36,846 --> 00:36:38,456
I wrote it well.

649
00:36:38,456 --> 00:36:41,036
- I actually wrote this five times.
- Really?

650
00:36:41,036 --> 00:36:43,266
I wasn't happy with the handwriting.

651
00:36:43,266 --> 00:36:44,446
I wrote it at work.

652
00:36:44,446 --> 00:36:47,226
- She's so cute.
- During a lunch break.

653
00:36:47,226 --> 00:36:51,026
I wrote it over and over again
because it didn't look right.

654
00:36:51,026 --> 00:36:53,726
Thank you so much. This is ridiculously nice.

655
00:36:54,546 --> 00:36:56,736
Put it near your head.

656
00:36:56,736 --> 00:36:58,686
So the plant takes away your worries.

657
00:36:58,686 --> 00:37:01,046
- You've got to be kidding.
- I'm moved.

658
00:37:01,046 --> 00:37:03,206
So ridiculously moved.

659
00:37:04,336 --> 00:37:07,346
- You gifted me a book, too.
- Right.

660
00:37:07,346 --> 00:37:09,226
I was so grateful for that.

661
00:37:09,226 --> 00:37:13,146
In Japan, you bought me ice cream and food.

662
00:37:13,146 --> 00:37:16,916
She already forgot about how he hurt her.

663
00:37:19,746 --> 00:37:22,986
There is a reason why I gifted you a plant.

664
00:37:23,966 --> 00:37:27,046
- What...
- What is it? I want to know.

665
00:37:27,046 --> 00:37:30,876
- You remind me of a plant somehow.
- He's like a plant?

666
00:37:30,876 --> 00:37:35,396
The color green suits you.
You're like a plant.

667
00:37:35,396 --> 00:37:40,096
- You are like a plant and a forest.
- What a huge compliment.

668
00:37:41,526 --> 00:37:42,776
[Hesitating]

669
00:37:42,776 --> 00:37:44,786
You're like...

670
00:37:46,756 --> 00:37:50,896
I just paused because I struggle
to say these things.

671
00:37:50,896 --> 00:37:53,346
You're like the sun. You're very bright.

672
00:37:53,346 --> 00:37:55,276
- Am I?
- You get photosynthesis.

673
00:37:55,276 --> 00:38:00,166
You radiate and brighten things for everyone.

674
00:38:01,836 --> 00:38:03,946
[Smiling]

675
00:38:06,236 --> 00:38:07,336
[Smiling]

676
00:38:08,166 --> 00:38:11,516
I'm so glad I came on this show.

677
00:38:11,516 --> 00:38:13,546
Why? In what way?

678
00:38:13,546 --> 00:38:16,036
Because I was able to meet you.

679
00:38:17,596 --> 00:38:20,006
[Dizzy]

680
00:38:20,006 --> 00:38:21,866
You just blurted out like that?

681
00:38:21,866 --> 00:38:23,706
That's how I feel.

682
00:38:24,296 --> 00:38:27,546
I think it's because I was able to meet you.

683
00:38:27,546 --> 00:38:29,836
- Really?
- Things are going great today.

684
00:38:29,836 --> 00:38:31,576
I mean it.

685
00:38:33,496 --> 00:38:36,016
He seems more affected than usual.

686
00:38:36,016 --> 00:38:38,816
Give me a turn signal.

687
00:38:38,816 --> 00:38:41,056
- Use the turn signal when you turn left.
- Okay.

688
00:38:41,056 --> 00:38:43,556
[Is there a turn signal for heartbeat?]

689
00:38:48,006 --> 00:38:51,186
Huh? My hand is shaking.

690
00:38:51,186 --> 00:38:53,996
- She said it casually, but...
- Her hand is shaking.

691
00:38:53,996 --> 00:38:55,976
Hold it, Seong Min.

692
00:38:55,976 --> 00:38:57,146
Seriously.

693
00:38:57,146 --> 00:39:04,476
[He keeps noticing her sincere heart]

694
00:39:04,476 --> 00:39:06,206
A precious connection?

695
00:39:07,986 --> 00:39:11,726
- Precious, so precious.
- A precious connection.

696
00:39:16,566 --> 00:39:21,466
[What kind of connection
will this conversation lead to?]

697
00:39:21,466 --> 00:39:22,626
I really don't know.

698
00:39:22,626 --> 00:39:25,356
Min Ju poured her heart out on this date.

699
00:39:25,356 --> 00:39:26,566
Totally.

700
00:39:26,566 --> 00:39:29,716
She's scraped the rest of her feelings

701
00:39:29,716 --> 00:39:33,126
and gave it to him all at once on this date.

702
00:39:33,126 --> 00:39:36,906
Meeting someone who expresses their feelings

703
00:39:36,906 --> 00:39:40,476
and wishes for your well-being
and happiness like this

704
00:39:40,476 --> 00:39:43,176
once in your life would be...

705
00:39:43,176 --> 00:39:44,616
- a rare event.
- Right.

706
00:39:44,616 --> 00:39:48,246
Some people never get to be loved like this.

707
00:39:48,246 --> 00:39:49,896
Right.

708
00:39:49,896 --> 00:39:52,396
I didn't. I have no memory of it.

709
00:39:52,396 --> 00:39:54,276
I know.

710
00:39:54,276 --> 00:39:59,016
Many people never meet someone
who loves them like this.

711
00:39:59,016 --> 00:40:02,656
If he doesn't see the value in her,

712
00:40:02,656 --> 00:40:06,446
- I hope they don't get together.
- Here we go again.

713
00:40:07,406 --> 00:40:09,676
Looks like they're not coming home.

714
00:40:09,676 --> 00:40:11,366
It's almost midnight.

715
00:40:11,366 --> 00:40:12,796
They haven't come home yet.

716
00:40:12,796 --> 00:40:14,466
It's 11:30 right now.

717
00:40:14,466 --> 00:40:15,936
No one's home yet.

718
00:40:15,936 --> 00:40:18,876
Everyone must be on a date.

719
00:40:21,526 --> 00:40:23,826
I couldn't bring myself to read it.

720
00:40:23,826 --> 00:40:26,356
That postcard right there.

721
00:40:26,356 --> 00:40:29,916
[A postcard is in Hamster's book]

722
00:40:29,916 --> 00:40:32,816
Didn't he put it in his own book?

723
00:40:32,816 --> 00:40:36,616
- No.
- Yu Gyeong wrote that postcard.

724
00:40:36,616 --> 00:40:38,606
That's the response he got.

725
00:40:38,606 --> 00:40:40,556
- Really?
- Yes.

726
00:40:41,966 --> 00:40:43,826
He asked two questions.

727
00:40:43,826 --> 00:40:46,036
Hamster is impressive.

728
00:40:46,656 --> 00:40:47,556
Who is it?

729
00:40:47,556 --> 00:40:50,026
- Hamster is so hardworking.
- He's spinning his wheel.

730
00:40:50,026 --> 00:40:52,196
- I wonder who is home.
- I wonder.

731
00:40:52,196 --> 00:40:54,246
- Who's home?
- Who's home?

732
00:40:55,166 --> 00:40:56,746
They're home.

733
00:40:56,746 --> 00:40:59,766
- I always end up sneaking in.
- I know.

734
00:41:00,606 --> 00:41:02,586
- They're home.
- They're back after a date.

735
00:41:02,586 --> 00:41:03,886
Hi.

736
00:41:03,886 --> 00:41:05,826
- Unni.
- Hi.

737
00:41:05,826 --> 00:41:07,726
- Min Ju is still excited.
- What's that?

738
00:41:07,726 --> 00:41:09,726
- Where were you?
- Where were you?

739
00:41:09,726 --> 00:41:11,736
- Where have you been?
- We ask where you were.

740
00:41:11,736 --> 00:41:13,326
We ran into each other here.

741
00:41:13,326 --> 00:41:14,906
- Stop lying.
- Stop lying.

742
00:41:14,906 --> 00:41:16,956
Nonsense! It's 11:30.

743
00:41:16,956 --> 00:41:18,686
[Changing direction
due to the loud complaint]

744
00:41:18,686 --> 00:41:20,066
They're freaking out.

745
00:41:20,066 --> 00:41:22,266
I worked late tonight.

746
00:41:22,266 --> 00:41:26,536
Why did he go inside on his own?
How ridiculous.

747
00:41:26,536 --> 00:41:27,626
He's the avoidant type.

748
00:41:27,626 --> 00:41:32,126
He is. He's the one
who asked all the questions.

749
00:41:32,126 --> 00:41:34,746
- Is he Hamster?
- We don't know who Hamster is.

750
00:41:34,746 --> 00:41:39,316
We don't, but it looks like he is.

751
00:41:39,316 --> 00:41:41,196
Mr. Hamster.

752
00:41:41,196 --> 00:41:43,126
He's Busy Hamster.

753
00:41:43,126 --> 00:41:45,366
He must be busy right now.

754
00:41:46,416 --> 00:41:48,476
[Wu Yeol and So Yun are back, too]

755
00:41:48,476 --> 00:41:50,006
What's with you guys?

756
00:41:50,006 --> 00:41:52,316
Why is everyone coming home in pairs?

757
00:41:52,316 --> 00:41:54,526
- What do you think?
- Who else came in a pair?

758
00:41:54,526 --> 00:41:57,016
Seong Min and Min Ju came back together.

759
00:41:57,016 --> 00:41:59,426
Is none of the girls home?

760
00:41:59,426 --> 00:42:01,306
You scared me.

761
00:42:01,306 --> 00:42:03,766
Why are you back so late?

762
00:42:03,766 --> 00:42:06,396
Where were you? You were all dressed up.

763
00:42:06,396 --> 00:42:08,816
I had a good time with a bad person.

764
00:42:10,256 --> 00:42:11,736
[Good time with a bad person]

765
00:42:11,736 --> 00:42:13,906
That's like the title of a drama.

766
00:42:13,906 --> 00:42:17,186
- You can write two songs with that.
- It's a title.

767
00:42:17,186 --> 00:42:19,896
- She's so clever, isn't she?
- Totally.

768
00:42:19,896 --> 00:42:23,206
Good time with a bad person?

769
00:42:23,206 --> 00:42:25,786
So Yun is so quick.

770
00:42:25,786 --> 00:42:28,516
- I have a gift for you.
- What is it?

771
00:42:28,516 --> 00:42:31,016
- I'm serious.
- Wow.

772
00:42:31,016 --> 00:42:33,416
- It's Valentine's Day.
- What?

773
00:42:33,416 --> 00:42:35,246
Are you trying to impress me?

774
00:42:35,246 --> 00:42:38,166
No, it's just Valentine's Day.

775
00:42:38,166 --> 00:42:40,736
- So Yun is so charming.
- Why won't you give me one?

776
00:42:40,736 --> 00:42:41,966
We don't get any?

777
00:42:41,966 --> 00:42:43,686
[Teasing]

778
00:42:44,706 --> 00:42:46,896
It's Valentine's Day.

779
00:42:46,896 --> 00:42:49,146
- What is it?
- What's in here?

780
00:42:49,146 --> 00:42:50,926
[Eye drop]

781
00:42:50,926 --> 00:42:52,826
- So cute.
- You brought so much.

782
00:42:52,826 --> 00:42:55,296
Thank you. I needed it.

783
00:42:58,836 --> 00:43:00,736
What did you do today?

784
00:43:00,736 --> 00:43:03,426
We ate and waited for you. We hung out.

785
00:43:03,426 --> 00:43:04,486
"Waited for you."

786
00:43:04,486 --> 00:43:06,646
I didn't know you weren't coming home.

787
00:43:06,646 --> 00:43:09,316
He looked upset just now.

788
00:43:10,026 --> 00:43:12,326
- Are you going in?
- To where?

789
00:43:12,326 --> 00:43:14,136
To the room? No.

790
00:43:20,796 --> 00:43:22,556
What time are you leaving tomorrow?

791
00:43:22,556 --> 00:43:25,826
I leave around 10 tomorrow.

792
00:43:26,516 --> 00:43:28,616
- Around 10?
- Yes.

793
00:43:32,166 --> 00:43:35,846
I'm not sure yet. It hasn't been decided.

794
00:43:41,746 --> 00:43:47,326
They don't have to tell us about their date.

795
00:43:47,326 --> 00:43:49,696
You can just tell.

796
00:43:49,696 --> 00:43:51,426
Yes.

797
00:43:52,746 --> 00:43:54,346
Right.

798
00:43:56,026 --> 00:43:58,326
[Fidgeting]

799
00:44:04,026 --> 00:44:05,796
That's when I felt it.

800
00:44:05,796 --> 00:44:07,316
That...

801
00:44:10,066 --> 00:44:13,446
I was noticing someone in that big group.

802
00:44:14,136 --> 00:44:17,756
You know when you can't help
but look that way.

803
00:44:18,376 --> 00:44:21,226
Wu Yeol ended things with her.

804
00:44:23,096 --> 00:44:25,606
I can't help but say less.

805
00:44:26,596 --> 00:44:28,026
Why?

806
00:44:29,946 --> 00:44:32,236
Why are you laughing?

807
00:44:35,176 --> 00:44:38,226
- Are you drinking?
- No, I'm going downstairs.

808
00:44:38,226 --> 00:44:39,526
[The conversation paused]

809
00:44:39,526 --> 00:44:41,276
I'll be in the room.

810
00:44:41,276 --> 00:44:43,286
What's the pencil sharpener for?

811
00:44:43,916 --> 00:44:45,686
I'm sharpening pencils.

812
00:44:47,676 --> 00:44:49,276
Is this it?

813
00:44:49,996 --> 00:44:51,936
Where are they?

814
00:45:03,796 --> 00:45:06,336
I'm tired.

815
00:45:10,966 --> 00:45:13,306
You must have been bored today.

816
00:45:13,306 --> 00:45:15,996
- Today? At home?
- Yes.

817
00:45:15,996 --> 00:45:19,416
Thankfully, Jun Hyeon was home.

818
00:45:19,416 --> 00:45:22,016
If he wasn't home,

819
00:45:22,016 --> 00:45:25,536
I would have been so sad.

820
00:45:26,436 --> 00:45:28,586
I wanted to come home early, too.

821
00:45:29,486 --> 00:45:31,776
But I knew.

822
00:45:31,776 --> 00:45:32,936
What do you mean?

823
00:45:32,936 --> 00:45:36,236
- I knew you'd come home late.
- Really? How?

824
00:45:36,236 --> 00:45:42,006
Based on our conversation this morning.

825
00:45:42,006 --> 00:45:43,446
What about it?

826
00:45:44,696 --> 00:45:47,286
You weren't able to tell me in detail.

827
00:45:47,286 --> 00:45:52,376
So, I knew you were going out tonight.

828
00:45:59,186 --> 00:46:05,586
[She was hoping to spend time alone together]

829
00:46:22,866 --> 00:46:26,626
I did the dishes with Jun Hyeon.

830
00:46:26,626 --> 00:46:28,776
I'm sorry.

831
00:46:31,066 --> 00:46:33,636
- I won't do it.
- What?

832
00:46:33,636 --> 00:46:37,346
I won't do the dishes with you anymore.

833
00:46:39,906 --> 00:46:41,556
Why not?

834
00:46:41,556 --> 00:46:44,166
- You'd better do all these dishes.
- I will.

835
00:46:44,166 --> 00:46:45,146
[Cute complaint]

836
00:46:45,146 --> 00:46:48,776
She's able to whine at him now.

837
00:46:58,416 --> 00:47:01,896
- I wanted to do the dishes.
- What did you do on the 11th and 12th?

838
00:47:01,896 --> 00:47:04,676
Didn't we drink on those days?

839
00:47:04,676 --> 00:47:08,326
There's nothing written
for the 11th and 12th.

840
00:47:08,326 --> 00:47:10,476
- What did we do?
- It stopped on the 11th.

841
00:47:10,476 --> 00:47:15,056
After work, it was around 4 a.m...

842
00:47:15,056 --> 00:47:19,606
- It's routine.
- I usually write it down, but it stopped.

843
00:47:24,816 --> 00:47:27,966
Are you hungry? Are you hungry?

844
00:47:27,966 --> 00:47:30,466
I think I'm addicted to this.

845
00:47:30,466 --> 00:47:32,876
I'm so tired.

846
00:47:33,656 --> 00:47:35,626
Is Min Ju not sleeping?

847
00:47:38,556 --> 00:47:39,806
[Peeping]

848
00:47:40,836 --> 00:47:43,026
[Pausing]

849
00:47:43,026 --> 00:47:46,396
I'm going to the first floor.

850
00:47:48,076 --> 00:47:51,256
- She walked by.
- To bother them.

851
00:47:54,826 --> 00:47:57,706
- They're bothered.
- It seems so.

852
00:47:59,566 --> 00:48:05,166
[Gyu Ri is in the living room alone]

853
00:48:08,876 --> 00:48:10,386
[Buzzing]

854
00:48:12,526 --> 00:48:18,876
[Dried Sweet Potato wants
to meet with Salt Bread]

855
00:48:18,876 --> 00:48:24,716
[He got a signal from Gyu Ri last night]

856
00:48:30,176 --> 00:48:31,916
[Mixed feelings]

857
00:48:31,916 --> 00:48:34,646
It's better to put an end to things quickly.

858
00:48:42,596 --> 00:48:44,226
Did you bring the snacks from earlier?

859
00:48:44,226 --> 00:48:46,586
- I left it downstairs.
- You did?

860
00:48:46,586 --> 00:48:48,456
[Wu Yeol is headed to the first floor]

861
00:48:48,456 --> 00:48:50,556
I'm sad. Give me an ice cream.

862
00:48:50,556 --> 00:48:52,456
Ice cream? Which one do you want?

863
00:48:52,456 --> 00:48:53,986
What do we have?

864
00:48:53,986 --> 00:48:56,806
What flavors do we have?

865
00:48:58,246 --> 00:49:00,136
[Looking]

866
00:49:01,066 --> 00:49:02,596
What is that?

867
00:49:02,596 --> 00:49:04,296
Greek yogurt.

868
00:49:09,716 --> 00:49:12,136
- What did you eat?
- He's sitting next to her.

869
00:49:12,136 --> 00:49:13,476
What's the deal?

870
00:49:14,576 --> 00:49:16,896
- Sounds good.
- I got paid.

871
00:49:17,706 --> 00:49:19,296
[Looking]

872
00:49:19,806 --> 00:49:22,786
- Give me the New Year money.
- Hold on.

873
00:49:22,786 --> 00:49:24,216
[Yu Gyeong is walking down the stairs]

874
00:49:24,216 --> 00:49:27,766
- Can I take three bows?
- That's not how it works.

875
00:49:27,766 --> 00:49:29,466
They're downstairs.

876
00:49:29,466 --> 00:49:32,296
- Why are we split up?
- I know.

877
00:49:33,496 --> 00:49:35,346
Why are you like that all the time?

878
00:49:35,346 --> 00:49:37,736
What are you talking about?

879
00:49:38,836 --> 00:49:40,706
Noona, you want to be like that?

880
00:49:40,706 --> 00:49:42,276
[Glancing]

881
00:49:42,276 --> 00:49:44,096
She saw them.

882
00:49:47,176 --> 00:49:49,826
So awkward. Gosh.

883
00:49:49,826 --> 00:49:52,886
Why is he sitting over there?

884
00:49:52,886 --> 00:49:55,066
What's the deal? Why?

885
00:49:55,066 --> 00:49:58,066
We're drinking in the kitchen tonight.

886
00:49:58,066 --> 00:49:59,976
Really?

887
00:50:01,796 --> 00:50:05,346
Why are you... Never mind.

888
00:50:05,346 --> 00:50:06,946
- What?
- I'll be over there.

889
00:50:06,946 --> 00:50:09,996
No, no. What, what, what?

890
00:50:12,506 --> 00:50:14,566
Get up, Wu Yeol.

891
00:50:15,746 --> 00:50:18,736
I was going to pick it up
on the way, but I got tired.

892
00:50:18,736 --> 00:50:21,386
[She's preoccupied with one thing only]

893
00:50:21,386 --> 00:50:24,036
This is giving her a headache again.

894
00:50:25,856 --> 00:50:29,266
What did you do? What did you do today?

895
00:50:29,266 --> 00:50:32,346
I had dinner after work.

896
00:50:32,346 --> 00:50:35,216
What was the dish tonight? Who cooked?

897
00:50:35,216 --> 00:50:38,106
I ate outside tonight, too.

898
00:50:39,226 --> 00:50:40,866
Was it a date?

899
00:50:41,806 --> 00:50:43,396
[Nodding]

900
00:50:43,946 --> 00:50:46,316
- With whom?
- So Yun.

901
00:50:54,906 --> 00:50:57,866
Are you used to receiving this now?

902
00:50:57,866 --> 00:51:01,876
- Sending and receiving it?
- The text?

903
00:51:01,876 --> 00:51:03,466
Am I used to it?

904
00:51:09,456 --> 00:51:12,506
I used to send it to you.

905
00:51:12,506 --> 00:51:15,636
And I know you used to send it to me, too.

906
00:51:16,406 --> 00:51:20,936
It felt like we had a hiatus.

907
00:51:22,546 --> 00:51:23,946
[Nodding]

908
00:51:23,946 --> 00:51:28,036
You know what I mean? When was it?

909
00:51:28,036 --> 00:51:32,956
I think we had a big hiatus
until the Japan trip.

910
00:51:38,686 --> 00:51:41,356
Through many dates,

911
00:51:42,976 --> 00:51:47,396
I wondered what version of myself

912
00:51:48,316 --> 00:51:52,746
I was most happy and satisfied with.

913
00:51:57,036 --> 00:52:01,136
I would feel the same way even if
I went back to the first day.

914
00:52:02,206 --> 00:52:06,556
My thoughts would be the same
as they are now, even if I went back.

915
00:52:08,676 --> 00:52:11,886
So, I'm not that upset about

916
00:52:11,886 --> 00:52:15,726
not being on so many dates.

917
00:52:17,256 --> 00:52:19,106
I'm being honest.

918
00:52:19,796 --> 00:52:23,706
I think our timing didn't work out.

919
00:52:26,296 --> 00:52:30,836
You seem a little too decided.

920
00:52:35,086 --> 00:52:41,266
I used to think I had decided on you, too.

921
00:52:42,696 --> 00:52:46,476
If you have decided on someone,

922
00:52:46,476 --> 00:52:48,616
am I not supposed to mess with you?

923
00:52:50,276 --> 00:52:52,436
[Pause]

924
00:53:03,956 --> 00:53:07,876
I went to check if everything was okay.
And they were there.

925
00:53:08,686 --> 00:53:11,866
- People are there.
- Yes, there are two.

926
00:53:13,726 --> 00:53:15,276
Let's drink.

927
00:53:17,086 --> 00:53:19,736
[Chugging the aloe drink]

928
00:53:19,736 --> 00:53:21,176
You're drunk.

929
00:53:21,986 --> 00:53:23,716
You'll get plastered with that.

930
00:53:23,716 --> 00:53:26,876
- I'm tired.
- What a drunk.

931
00:53:31,036 --> 00:53:39,136
[Feelings are getting tangled up]

932
00:53:44,416 --> 00:53:46,426
This is fun.

933
00:53:48,616 --> 00:53:50,876
Let's have fun.

934
00:53:52,786 --> 00:53:55,776
We went out for dinner already.

935
00:53:55,776 --> 00:53:57,496
What do you want to do?

936
00:54:06,066 --> 00:54:10,906
I thought of an amazing answer.

937
00:54:14,266 --> 00:54:16,506
Want to watch "Decision to Leave"?

938
00:54:18,096 --> 00:54:22,746
[Wait, time out]

939
00:54:22,746 --> 00:54:25,816
[What did we just hear?]

940
00:54:25,816 --> 00:54:27,506
Gyu Ri is something else.

941
00:54:27,506 --> 00:54:29,016
[Going home due to a shock]

942
00:54:29,016 --> 00:54:31,836
[The taping is about to be canceled]

943
00:54:31,836 --> 00:54:34,676
I feel like I just got hit in the chest.

944
00:54:34,676 --> 00:54:36,696
I can't hear my heartbeat right now.

945
00:54:36,696 --> 00:54:38,146
[Coughing]

946
00:54:38,886 --> 00:54:41,076
Want to watch "Decision to Leave"?

947
00:54:41,076 --> 00:54:43,216
I got the chills.

948
00:54:44,716 --> 00:54:47,836
I got the chills on the back of my head.

949
00:54:50,886 --> 00:54:53,536
[The night is getting more chaotic]

950
00:54:53,536 --> 00:54:55,976
Time is going by quicker than last night.

951
00:54:55,976 --> 00:54:57,736
This is considered quick.

952
00:54:57,736 --> 00:54:59,346
But I joined recently.

953
00:54:59,346 --> 00:55:02,676
This is considered quick. You joined later.

954
00:55:04,916 --> 00:55:06,866
Yu Gyeong.

955
00:55:12,716 --> 00:55:19,236
[What are they thinking about?]

956
00:55:19,886 --> 00:55:22,746
The date is Saturday at 9.

957
00:55:30,116 --> 00:55:32,086
Are you very tired tonight, too?

958
00:55:32,086 --> 00:55:34,126
- Tonight?
- Yes.

959
00:55:34,126 --> 00:55:36,066
I think I am.

960
00:55:36,826 --> 00:55:38,466
I'll think about it.

961
00:55:38,466 --> 00:55:41,796
- I just said it.
- Don't just throw it out there.

962
00:55:41,796 --> 00:55:43,516
[There are more questions she wants to ask]

963
00:55:43,516 --> 00:55:45,846
You look tired.

964
00:55:47,576 --> 00:55:50,196
Will Wu Yeol be okay?

965
00:55:50,196 --> 00:55:52,006
Wu Yeol, are you going to be okay?

966
00:55:52,006 --> 00:55:54,506
Can I watch from the back?

967
00:55:54,506 --> 00:55:58,146
This must be one of the biggest storms

968
00:55:58,146 --> 00:56:00,016
we've had on Heart Signal 5.

969
00:56:00,016 --> 00:56:02,996
It's more than that.
This is the biggest one yet.

970
00:56:02,996 --> 00:56:05,816
I've never freaked out
and walked around before.

971
00:56:05,816 --> 00:56:10,736
Gyu Ri headed downstairs, saying,
"I'll go to the first floor."

972
00:56:10,736 --> 00:56:14,026
I also thought that meant,
"Come downstairs, Wu Yeol."

973
00:56:14,026 --> 00:56:16,566
- I felt that.
- And your hunch was correct.

974
00:56:16,566 --> 00:56:18,546
What's going on?

975
00:56:23,766 --> 00:56:26,866
- Did Jun Hyeon ask Yu Gyeong out?
- Or Seong Min.

976
00:56:26,866 --> 00:56:29,706
[Yu Gyeong is waiting for her date]

977
00:56:33,026 --> 00:56:35,536
It's a bookstore. Must be Seong Min.

978
00:56:35,536 --> 00:56:41,636
[Yu Gyeong's date is Seong Min]

979
00:56:42,346 --> 00:56:43,776
What?

980
00:56:47,126 --> 00:56:49,456
What are you doing here?

981
00:56:49,456 --> 00:56:52,076
[Smiling]

982
00:56:53,686 --> 00:56:56,356
Hamster?

983
00:56:56,356 --> 00:56:59,196
[Yu Gyeong wanted to meet Busy Hamster]

984
00:56:59,196 --> 00:57:01,056
Who are you here to meet?

985
00:57:01,056 --> 00:57:03,136
They didn't tell me who I was meeting with.

986
00:57:03,136 --> 00:57:05,476
What, really?

987
00:57:05,476 --> 00:57:09,106
- I see. You came without knowing.
- I had no clue.

988
00:57:09,106 --> 00:57:12,036
But I did.

989
00:57:12,036 --> 00:57:16,176
I was like, "Who could be Hamster?"

990
00:57:16,176 --> 00:57:17,896
Were they told to come to the bookstore?

991
00:57:17,896 --> 00:57:21,596
- I was reading this while waiting for you.
- How long did you wait?

992
00:57:21,596 --> 00:57:23,606
I didn't wait that long.

993
00:57:23,606 --> 00:57:25,136
[Busy Hamster was Seong Min]

994
00:57:26,106 --> 00:57:27,756
Did they choose each other?

995
00:57:27,756 --> 00:57:30,396
They chose each other.

996
00:57:30,396 --> 00:57:31,706
Isn't this it?

997
00:57:31,706 --> 00:57:35,796
They had a reason to meet because
they've been exchanging notes.

998
00:57:35,796 --> 00:57:37,926
I'm hungry.

999
00:57:37,926 --> 00:57:40,386
We're at a very nice place tonight.

1000
00:57:40,386 --> 00:57:42,366
- Very nice.
- Very nice.

1001
00:57:42,366 --> 00:57:44,096
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

1002
00:57:44,096 --> 00:57:46,606
Have a look at this.

1003
00:57:48,196 --> 00:57:51,706
The famous ones are truffle cheese...

1004
00:57:51,706 --> 00:57:53,196
Sounds good.

1005
00:57:53,196 --> 00:57:55,136
- Here you go.
- Thank you.

1006
00:57:55,136 --> 00:57:57,766
I recommend having it with cilantro.

1007
00:57:57,766 --> 00:57:59,686
- Do you want the cilantro on top?
- Yes.

1008
00:57:59,686 --> 00:58:01,636
- Do you want a lot?
- Just enough.

1009
00:58:01,636 --> 00:58:03,166
Just enough?

1010
00:58:05,056 --> 00:58:06,716
- Is that too much?
- No.

1011
00:58:06,716 --> 00:58:08,936
- It's not too much.
- Okay.

1012
00:58:08,936 --> 00:58:10,546
Thank you so much.

1013
00:58:10,546 --> 00:58:12,616
Thanks for the meal.

1014
00:58:13,216 --> 00:58:14,446
[Big bite]

1015
00:58:17,386 --> 00:58:19,186
That's tasty.

1016
00:58:19,186 --> 00:58:20,876
It's warm.

1017
00:58:22,966 --> 00:58:23,936
[Smiling]

1018
00:58:23,936 --> 00:58:25,746
- How about the wine now?
- Yes.

1019
00:58:25,746 --> 00:58:27,256
- I agree.
- Good.

1020
00:58:27,256 --> 00:58:28,546
[Cheers]

1021
00:58:32,606 --> 00:58:34,326
[Staring]

1022
00:58:36,996 --> 00:58:39,176
I have a lot to say...

1023
00:58:40,176 --> 00:58:43,726
- about Busy Hamster.
- Good.

1024
00:58:44,736 --> 00:58:47,846
Take your time. Eat first.

1025
00:58:55,996 --> 00:58:59,576
Now, I want to...

1026
00:59:03,916 --> 00:59:07,586
directly face our...

1027
00:59:07,586 --> 00:59:10,656
conversations and dates.

1028
00:59:10,656 --> 00:59:12,516
Yes, she's been avoiding it.

1029
00:59:12,516 --> 00:59:14,646
Directly face them?

1030
00:59:14,646 --> 00:59:16,396
That's the word she chose.

1031
00:59:16,396 --> 00:59:18,556
It means she's been avoiding it.

1032
00:59:18,556 --> 00:59:20,126
I've been wanting to talk to you.

1033
00:59:20,126 --> 00:59:22,476
Right, they haven't had a real talk.

1034
00:59:22,476 --> 00:59:24,886
- I have been wanting to.
- That's good.

1035
00:59:24,886 --> 00:59:26,466
Me, too.

1036
00:59:30,366 --> 00:59:32,706
Take your time. You don't have to.

1037
00:59:32,706 --> 00:59:35,736
You can if that's what you want.

1038
00:59:35,736 --> 00:59:40,286
- Seong Min speaks in such a dry manner.
- Yeah, his tone.

1039
00:59:42,906 --> 00:59:49,296
I've been getting texts from
Hamster for the first few days.

1040
00:59:49,296 --> 00:59:51,906
That's why I didn't think it was you.

1041
00:59:53,756 --> 00:59:56,026
- Didn't you have an idea?
- No.

1042
00:59:56,026 --> 00:59:57,406
Really?

1043
00:59:58,096 --> 01:00:00,076
I had no idea.

1044
01:00:00,076 --> 01:00:03,386
- Really?
- And then I realized halfway through.

1045
01:00:03,386 --> 01:00:06,746
- I found out later.
- She was mistaken.

1046
01:00:09,756 --> 01:00:15,056
At first, I thought, "Why?"

1047
01:00:16,636 --> 01:00:20,056
- But...
- "Why?" is not a positive reaction.

1048
01:00:20,056 --> 01:00:23,446
- I was genuinely surprised.
- Surprised?

1049
01:00:23,446 --> 01:00:25,646
The more I thought about it,

1050
01:00:25,646 --> 01:00:28,916
- the more grateful I was.
- She can't be direct.

1051
01:00:31,526 --> 01:00:33,136
You know,

1052
01:00:33,896 --> 01:00:35,896
so far,

1053
01:00:35,896 --> 01:00:38,896
I've liked people who showed interest in me.

1054
01:00:38,896 --> 01:00:41,316
And I've been dating those people.

1055
01:00:42,596 --> 01:00:46,936
That's what I thought,
and I thought the same thing...

1056
01:00:48,546 --> 01:00:51,506
would happen here, and I still do.

1057
01:00:52,296 --> 01:00:56,866
But sometimes I no longer feel that way.

1058
01:00:56,866 --> 01:00:57,966
Then...

1059
01:00:57,966 --> 01:01:00,736
It means she doesn't fall for someone
just because he likes her.

1060
01:01:00,736 --> 01:01:04,796
[She's not able to finish her sentence]

1061
01:01:05,526 --> 01:01:09,586
I like someone who likes me,

1062
01:01:09,586 --> 01:01:12,986
- but there's someone I like more.
- That's right.

1063
01:01:12,986 --> 01:01:15,316
What she says now is important.

1064
01:01:16,256 --> 01:01:19,126
- This place is full of exceptions.
- "Full of exceptions."

1065
01:01:19,126 --> 01:01:21,576
She basically turned him down.

1066
01:01:28,966 --> 01:01:33,456
I've been expressing my interest in you,

1067
01:01:34,716 --> 01:01:38,576
but we never crossed paths.

1068
01:01:39,306 --> 01:01:42,566
I found that to be a shame.

1069
01:01:43,866 --> 01:01:47,776
I was hoping to have a serious conversation

1070
01:01:47,776 --> 01:01:50,946
or time alone with you.

1071
01:01:53,136 --> 01:01:56,996
I even thought, "I guess this is
not going to work out."

1072
01:01:56,996 --> 01:01:58,806
- It's not going to happen.
- Really?

1073
01:01:58,806 --> 01:02:01,636
Yes, he could have thought that.

1074
01:02:01,636 --> 01:02:04,116
I thought it wasn't going to go that way.

1075
01:02:04,116 --> 01:02:08,296
- Timing is so important.
- I know, stuff like that.

1076
01:02:08,296 --> 01:02:10,716
And since we're staying with other people,

1077
01:02:10,716 --> 01:02:13,996
I became aware of what they might think.

1078
01:02:13,996 --> 01:02:17,366
I tend to suppress my feelings.

1079
01:02:17,366 --> 01:02:20,716
But I've been trying not to be that way here.

1080
01:02:20,716 --> 01:02:25,566
He's been forging ahead,
but he hasn't said anything.

1081
01:02:25,566 --> 01:02:27,956
I think no one knows for sure.

1082
01:02:27,956 --> 01:02:31,066
That comes up a lot.

1083
01:02:33,876 --> 01:02:36,406
He's trying to enter through a crack.

1084
01:02:39,876 --> 01:02:44,906
[Seong Min is trying to go on that path]

1085
01:02:44,906 --> 01:02:48,536
According to what Yu Gyeong said,

1086
01:02:48,536 --> 01:02:52,186
she has liked the people who liked her,
but there are exceptions.

1087
01:02:52,186 --> 01:02:53,746
Right, she made it clear.

1088
01:02:53,746 --> 01:02:56,106
She met him to tell him that.

1089
01:02:56,106 --> 01:03:00,446
He understood it, too. But even so,

1090
01:03:00,446 --> 01:03:03,296
he was like,
"You never know what will happen."

1091
01:03:03,296 --> 01:03:05,286
And I...

1092
01:03:05,286 --> 01:03:06,746
What?

1093
01:03:06,746 --> 01:03:09,556
I'm sorry. Why am I laughing?

1094
01:03:09,556 --> 01:03:11,986
I found this sad because

1095
01:03:11,986 --> 01:03:15,166
I think Yu Gyeong had Min Ju in mind.

1096
01:03:15,166 --> 01:03:17,296
She wanted him...

1097
01:03:17,296 --> 01:03:20,556
to be good to Unni more than anything.

1098
01:03:20,556 --> 01:03:24,486
She had no reason to meet him otherwise.

1099
01:03:24,486 --> 01:03:26,186
She must have felt many emotions.

1100
01:03:26,186 --> 01:03:30,706
She decided to reject the men
who were interested in her.

1101
01:03:30,706 --> 01:03:33,446
Especially Seong Min, whom Min Ju likes.

1102
01:03:33,446 --> 01:03:35,656
He's still pursuing her hard.

1103
01:03:35,656 --> 01:03:37,996
You know that he's been suppressing it.

1104
01:03:37,996 --> 01:03:41,126
You keep saying that, but when exactly?

1105
01:03:41,126 --> 01:03:44,706
Even if she were to consider other men,

1106
01:03:44,706 --> 01:03:46,536
she wouldn't consider Seong Min.

1107
01:03:46,536 --> 01:03:49,666
She already decided that.

1108
01:03:49,666 --> 01:03:52,286
But Seong Min decided to tell her anyway.

1109
01:03:52,286 --> 01:03:54,156
- Yu Gyeong is at fault here.
- Why?

1110
01:03:54,156 --> 01:03:57,906
She shouldn't have dolled up
if that was the purpose of this.

1111
01:03:57,906 --> 01:04:01,136
It's being proper. She can't look bad.
That'd be worse.

1112
01:04:01,136 --> 01:04:03,616
She was born pretty.
What could she do about it?

1113
01:04:03,616 --> 01:04:06,126
She can't help being pretty.

1114
01:04:08,306 --> 01:04:11,426
[Seongsu-dong, Seongdong-gu]

1115
01:04:11,426 --> 01:04:14,026
[Seo Won is waiting for his date]

1116
01:04:18,166 --> 01:04:19,586
Who is it?

1117
01:04:21,236 --> 01:04:22,236
[Smiling]

1118
01:04:22,236 --> 01:04:25,236
[He's on a date with So Yun today]

1119
01:04:25,236 --> 01:04:28,226
What are you doing on Friday?

1120
01:04:28,226 --> 01:04:29,396
What are you doing?

1121
01:04:29,396 --> 01:04:31,866
I want to hang out with you.

1122
01:04:31,866 --> 01:04:35,076
- So Yun asked him out.
- I need to check my schedule.

1123
01:04:35,076 --> 01:04:39,886
It wasn't a nickname date.
She just asked him out.

1124
01:04:39,886 --> 01:04:41,086
[Tap, tap]

1125
01:04:42,576 --> 01:04:46,796
[Preparing for a date, feeling excited]

1126
01:04:48,706 --> 01:04:50,936
She wants to get to know other people now.

1127
01:04:50,936 --> 01:04:52,946
Walk back. Walk back.

1128
01:04:54,156 --> 01:04:56,136
Walk back. Walk back.

1129
01:04:59,096 --> 01:05:01,396
- Hi.
- Hi.

1130
01:05:01,396 --> 01:05:03,206
Did you wait long?

1131
01:05:03,206 --> 01:05:07,586
A little? Long enough. This way.

1132
01:05:07,586 --> 01:05:11,956
Seo Won is great. So Yun will recognize that.

1133
01:05:11,956 --> 01:05:13,796
Long time no see.

1134
01:05:15,346 --> 01:05:20,936
[They haven't had a date in a long time]

1135
01:05:20,936 --> 01:05:22,856
Is chuck flap tail good?

1136
01:05:22,856 --> 01:05:26,096
- It's absolutely delicious.
- So cute.

1137
01:05:26,096 --> 01:05:29,086
I love everything.
I can't get enough of beef.

1138
01:05:29,806 --> 01:05:31,666
Let's get a set, then.

1139
01:05:33,516 --> 01:05:35,296
Are you good at grilling?

1140
01:05:35,296 --> 01:05:36,606
I'm not.

1141
01:05:36,606 --> 01:05:39,646
I keep flipping because I'm impatient.

1142
01:05:39,646 --> 01:05:41,956
You have to wait before you flip.

1143
01:05:41,956 --> 01:05:43,846
What's so funny?

1144
01:05:45,356 --> 01:05:46,786
So pretty.

1145
01:05:48,206 --> 01:05:50,166
That looks good.

1146
01:05:50,166 --> 01:05:51,666
I'll look forward to it.

1147
01:05:52,326 --> 01:05:55,326
Do you like burnt or raw meat?

1148
01:05:55,326 --> 01:05:57,926
- I like it less cooked.
- Less cooked.

1149
01:05:57,926 --> 01:06:01,546
- Make it medium rare, please.
- Medium rare?

1150
01:06:01,546 --> 01:06:05,176
It's more like well done.
The flame is strong.

1151
01:06:05,176 --> 01:06:08,736
- It's okay. I eat anything.
- Really?

1152
01:06:08,736 --> 01:06:10,746
Don't be discouraged.

1153
01:06:14,296 --> 01:06:16,116
Thank you.

1154
01:06:16,846 --> 01:06:19,746
Tell me how it is.

1155
01:06:22,796 --> 01:06:23,946
[Moved]

1156
01:06:23,946 --> 01:06:26,666
- Is it good?
- He must've done a good job.

1157
01:06:27,976 --> 01:06:30,396
- It's delicious.
- Really?

1158
01:06:31,506 --> 01:06:33,946
[He keeps handing her more]

1159
01:06:39,116 --> 01:06:41,336
- Are you eating a lot?
- Yes.

1160
01:06:41,336 --> 01:06:43,566
I want you to eat more.

1161
01:06:43,566 --> 01:06:44,836
Don't worry.

1162
01:06:45,766 --> 01:06:47,786
Daebak. She looks just like Shim Eun Ha.

1163
01:06:47,786 --> 01:06:50,536
- Let me try some.
- Try it.

1164
01:06:52,426 --> 01:06:54,396
They're feeding each other.

1165
01:06:54,396 --> 01:06:56,656
Is it good? It's good, huh?

1166
01:06:56,656 --> 01:06:58,736
It's so good.

1167
01:06:58,736 --> 01:07:00,746
Don't cry.

1168
01:07:04,316 --> 01:07:06,986
Nothing comforts you more than meat.

1169
01:07:06,986 --> 01:07:08,446
It's hot.

1170
01:07:13,076 --> 01:07:15,346
How was the date yesterday?

1171
01:07:15,346 --> 01:07:17,716
- I've been wanting to ask.
- Yesterday?

1172
01:07:18,536 --> 01:07:21,826
You looked so happy yesterday.

1173
01:07:21,826 --> 01:07:24,666
- She felt relieved, more like.
- But that's...

1174
01:07:27,206 --> 01:07:31,756
because I haven't drunk in a while.
I was in a good mood.

1175
01:07:32,766 --> 01:07:34,386
With Wu Yeol?

1176
01:07:36,266 --> 01:07:37,636
What?

1177
01:07:37,636 --> 01:07:39,816
Yes, it was nice.

1178
01:07:39,816 --> 01:07:40,956
It makes you smile just thinking about him?

1179
01:07:40,956 --> 01:07:42,996
[Teasing]

1180
01:07:42,996 --> 01:07:44,816
Oh, come on.

1181
01:07:44,816 --> 01:07:46,326
Sorry.

1182
01:07:48,826 --> 01:07:51,086
You can draw on the wine glasses.

1183
01:07:51,086 --> 01:07:53,016
- Wow, thank you.
- Thank you.

1184
01:07:53,016 --> 01:07:54,886
They let you draw on the wine glasses.

1185
01:07:54,886 --> 01:07:58,086
- Let's draw each other.
- You want to draw each other?

1186
01:07:58,086 --> 01:07:59,806
[Shy]

1187
01:08:03,206 --> 01:08:07,036
[Totally focused]

1188
01:08:08,946 --> 01:08:11,576
Let me know when you're done.
I'll keep mine covered.

1189
01:08:12,466 --> 01:08:14,046
Did you write something?

1190
01:08:14,046 --> 01:08:15,576
Of course.

1191
01:08:15,576 --> 01:08:19,286
- It's my message to you.
- A message for me?

1192
01:08:19,286 --> 01:08:21,626
I think of this when I think of you.

1193
01:08:21,626 --> 01:08:23,896
There's something I want to tell you.

1194
01:08:25,516 --> 01:08:27,136
This is fun.

1195
01:08:27,136 --> 01:08:28,376
[Alert]

1196
01:08:28,376 --> 01:08:29,526
[Looking away]

1197
01:08:30,456 --> 01:08:32,276
So cute.

1198
01:08:32,916 --> 01:08:34,856
[Exchanging the messages for each other]

1199
01:08:36,466 --> 01:08:37,616
They're swapping them.

1200
01:08:37,616 --> 01:08:39,626
You have great taste.

1201
01:08:40,316 --> 01:08:41,796
I really mean it.

1202
01:08:41,796 --> 01:08:43,296
"Come home earlier."

1203
01:08:43,296 --> 01:08:45,026
"Come home earlier." That's so cute.

1204
01:08:45,026 --> 01:08:46,796
That's so cute.

1205
01:08:47,906 --> 01:08:49,836
"Be strong."

1206
01:08:49,836 --> 01:08:52,236
- That's a good message.
- "Be strong, So Yun."

1207
01:08:52,236 --> 01:08:53,896
It sounds like he knows her situation.

1208
01:08:53,896 --> 01:08:56,836
This is kind of moving.

1209
01:08:58,036 --> 01:09:00,326
Seo Won knows everything.

1210
01:09:00,326 --> 01:09:01,926
Cheers.

1211
01:09:03,676 --> 01:09:06,026
The word "Gusseora"* means
(Be strong)

1212
01:09:07,276 --> 01:09:10,996
to stay true to your intentions

1213
01:09:10,996 --> 01:09:15,656
without backing down and keep charging ahead.

1214
01:09:16,546 --> 01:09:20,946
From the moment I first met you until now,

1215
01:09:22,456 --> 01:09:24,406
you're doing a great job.

1216
01:09:25,346 --> 01:09:27,916
You fit the meaning of the word
"gusseora" perfectly.

1217
01:09:27,916 --> 01:09:32,606
But I'm worried you might hold back
on what is your strength

1218
01:09:32,606 --> 01:09:36,466
because you care too much
about what others think

1219
01:09:36,466 --> 01:09:41,106
or worry about becoming a burden to them.

1220
01:09:41,106 --> 01:09:43,636
I hope you stay gusseora.

1221
01:09:44,526 --> 01:09:46,276
I'm tearing up.

1222
01:09:52,046 --> 01:09:54,196
[Stares]

1223
01:09:55,496 --> 01:09:59,146
[Feeling down after returning home]

1224
01:10:00,966 --> 01:10:03,046
Why are you picking at your food, Noona?

1225
01:10:04,036 --> 01:10:06,156
No, I did. I did it.

1226
01:10:06,156 --> 01:10:08,536
He's an altruistic person.

1227
01:10:08,536 --> 01:10:11,236
[Strangely reassured by Seo Won]

1228
01:10:11,866 --> 01:10:14,496
So Yun is feminine.

1229
01:10:14,496 --> 01:10:16,826
She's not just soft, she's slippery.

1230
01:10:16,826 --> 01:10:19,256
- Why do you think that?
- How did he know?

1231
01:10:19,256 --> 01:10:20,816
I can just see it.

1232
01:10:20,816 --> 01:10:23,126
People like that share a trait.

1233
01:10:23,126 --> 01:10:24,506
I wrote it down.

1234
01:10:24,506 --> 01:10:26,966
"Seems cold-hearted, but she's
actually very warm-hearted."

1235
01:10:26,966 --> 01:10:29,576
He's moving her in every possible way.

1236
01:10:29,576 --> 01:10:34,456
I have a friend I'm really close to
who is a lot like you.

1237
01:10:34,456 --> 01:10:40,116
While they might come across
as cold and straightforward,

1238
01:10:40,116 --> 01:10:42,836
they struggle on their own.

1239
01:10:42,836 --> 01:10:48,536
It made me realize you're the same
type of person.

1240
01:10:50,186 --> 01:10:51,796
That's interesting.

1241
01:10:53,936 --> 01:10:58,806
No one ever recognized that about me.

1242
01:10:58,806 --> 01:11:00,626
No one did.

1243
01:11:02,176 --> 01:11:06,946
It's the first time someone has
recognized that in such a short time.

1244
01:11:06,946 --> 01:11:11,266
People who seem strong on the
outside are usually tender-hearted.

1245
01:11:16,966 --> 01:11:18,186
[Glances]

1246
01:11:19,456 --> 01:11:20,666
What?

1247
01:11:20,666 --> 01:11:21,316
[Shakes head]

1248
01:11:24,326 --> 01:11:27,526
You went on a date
with Gyu Ri yesterday, right?

1249
01:11:27,526 --> 01:11:29,836
- I did.
- Did you enjoy it?

1250
01:11:30,506 --> 01:11:31,706
I did.

1251
01:11:32,416 --> 01:11:34,946
We got to know each other
a little better yesterday.

1252
01:11:34,946 --> 01:11:37,406
- Oh, really?
- Yeah.

1253
01:11:41,426 --> 01:11:44,646
What do you usually talk about with Gyu Ri?

1254
01:11:44,646 --> 01:11:46,356
- With Gyu Ri?
- Yeah.

1255
01:11:47,896 --> 01:11:50,526
We talked about some books.

1256
01:11:51,526 --> 01:11:53,326
Core values?

1257
01:11:53,326 --> 01:11:58,296
And our outlook on relationships and love.

1258
01:11:58,296 --> 01:12:00,476
Values. That is important.

1259
01:12:00,476 --> 01:12:03,666
What do you talk about on your dates?

1260
01:12:03,666 --> 01:12:07,196
I can't even begin to imagine with you.

1261
01:12:08,736 --> 01:12:10,746
On my dates?

1262
01:12:12,326 --> 01:12:14,726
I think I avoided deep conversations.

1263
01:12:14,726 --> 01:12:16,106
Why?

1264
01:12:17,266 --> 01:12:21,226
Honestly, I'm very curious about my dates.

1265
01:12:21,226 --> 01:12:22,836
But...

1266
01:12:25,616 --> 01:12:29,836
everyone seemed so shocked when I asked
about their ideal types on the first day.

1267
01:12:29,836 --> 01:12:32,276
It's making me think before I speak.

1268
01:12:32,276 --> 01:12:33,336
Before you ask?

1269
01:12:33,336 --> 01:12:38,936
I worried I might put them on the spot,
so I ended up holding myself back.

1270
01:12:39,846 --> 01:12:42,316
It's natural to ask if you're curious.

1271
01:12:45,056 --> 01:12:47,586
The thing with me is

1272
01:12:47,586 --> 01:12:53,016
once I fall for someone,
I don't notice anyone else.

1273
01:12:53,016 --> 01:12:55,656
- That's true.
- No matter how great the person is.

1274
01:12:55,656 --> 01:12:58,336
They become blurred out for me.

1275
01:12:59,786 --> 01:13:03,386
I only have eyes for the person I like.

1276
01:13:03,386 --> 01:13:07,626
But since we live together
and hang out all the time,

1277
01:13:07,626 --> 01:13:09,146
Right, right.

1278
01:13:09,146 --> 01:13:12,806
I discover revelatory qualities about them.

1279
01:13:12,806 --> 01:13:15,576
"He wasn't at first, but why
does he look so handsome now?"

1280
01:13:15,576 --> 01:13:17,536
[Cracking up]

1281
01:13:20,756 --> 01:13:23,086
"Was he always this handsome?"

1282
01:13:24,136 --> 01:13:27,086
[A few days earlier]

1283
01:13:27,676 --> 01:13:31,156
- I just got here.
- You got home so quietly.

1284
01:13:31,156 --> 01:13:35,376
What did everyone do today?
I got off work at around 9, 10.

1285
01:13:35,376 --> 01:13:37,046
He sure is handsome.

1286
01:13:37,046 --> 01:13:39,416
Every person who comes right now is precious.

1287
01:13:39,416 --> 01:13:41,366
When did she steal glances at Seo Won?

1288
01:13:41,366 --> 01:13:43,156
[So Yun sees Seo Won in a new light]

1289
01:13:44,386 --> 01:13:45,786
[Shy]

1290
01:13:45,786 --> 01:13:48,026
So their face transforms?

1291
01:13:48,026 --> 01:13:51,066
- It does for me.
- They weren't handsome before...

1292
01:13:51,066 --> 01:13:54,506
Regardless of whether they're
handsome or ugly objectively,

1293
01:13:54,506 --> 01:13:58,256
- according to my type.
- Right. Your personal type.

1294
01:13:58,256 --> 01:14:00,946
That's really honest of you.

1295
01:14:00,946 --> 01:14:03,386
I know what she's talking about.

1296
01:14:03,386 --> 01:14:08,446
It was hard for me to accept that at first.

1297
01:14:09,226 --> 01:14:13,516
- You were taken aback, huh? Hilarious.
- Yeah.

1298
01:14:13,516 --> 01:14:17,556
You know that feeling when your eyes lock?

1299
01:14:19,046 --> 01:14:20,606
- That feeling?
- Yeah.

1300
01:14:23,616 --> 01:14:25,746
You're such a girl!

1301
01:14:27,786 --> 01:14:30,516
You're killing me, Noona.

1302
01:14:31,986 --> 01:14:35,386
It could be one-sided, of course.

1303
01:14:36,136 --> 01:14:39,986
- You know that fluttery feeling?
- She's so cute.

1304
01:14:39,986 --> 01:14:43,916
I totally get you! My heart flutters.

1305
01:14:44,596 --> 01:14:48,166
But it was the first time I felt that way

1306
01:14:48,166 --> 01:14:51,706
after getting to know them
and not at first sight.

1307
01:14:51,706 --> 01:14:57,396
That's why I'm being careful about
expressing my feelings.

1308
01:15:00,006 --> 01:15:04,676
I'm being more cautious
about expressing myself.

1309
01:15:05,466 --> 01:15:10,566
But I'm internally conflicted since
there's not much time left.

1310
01:15:10,566 --> 01:15:12,936
- You feel rushed.
- "What should I do?"

1311
01:15:12,936 --> 01:15:16,506
"Should I just confess my feelings?"

1312
01:15:16,506 --> 01:15:20,876
These thoughts are clashing in my head.

1313
01:15:27,386 --> 01:15:29,286
Let's do our best.

1314
01:15:31,596 --> 01:15:34,976
Even if it doesn't end up
the way we want it to,

1315
01:15:34,976 --> 01:15:39,266
regretting what could've been
seems so foolish to me.

1316
01:15:39,266 --> 01:15:40,716
I felt the same way all this time.

1317
01:15:40,716 --> 01:15:43,666
But I've made up my mind now.

1318
01:15:47,006 --> 01:15:49,706
There's something I want to ask you.

1319
01:15:50,836 --> 01:15:52,836
Hold on.

1320
01:15:52,836 --> 01:15:54,876
Why does that make me nervous?

1321
01:15:54,876 --> 01:15:57,986
It's understandable
since it's coming from So Yun.

1322
01:15:57,986 --> 01:16:01,806
I'm ready, so let me know when you are.

1323
01:16:03,016 --> 01:16:04,926
It might take a while.

1324
01:16:04,926 --> 01:16:06,646
No, go ahead.

1325
01:16:08,186 --> 01:16:10,996
How did you feel about me on our first date?

1326
01:16:11,936 --> 01:16:13,736
- Our first date?
- Yeah.

1327
01:16:13,736 --> 01:16:15,376
At that tea house.

1328
01:16:22,926 --> 01:16:25,736
- It was fun.
- Fun?

1329
01:16:27,526 --> 01:16:29,386
It was really fun.

1330
01:16:33,626 --> 01:16:37,146
It's a fun memory that will stick with me.

1331
01:16:41,206 --> 01:16:44,176
[Their night deepens]

1332
01:16:44,916 --> 01:16:47,146
[They visit an arcade]

1333
01:16:47,146 --> 01:16:49,066
This looks fun!

1334
01:16:49,066 --> 01:16:51,026
I played two rounds of LoL.*
(League of Legends)

1335
01:16:51,026 --> 01:16:53,116
Huh? Do you play LoL?

1336
01:16:53,116 --> 01:16:55,136
Her ideal man is a good gamer.

1337
01:16:55,136 --> 01:16:57,046
- Really?
- What they both liked.

1338
01:16:57,046 --> 01:16:58,786
I can just take her to one place on a date.

1339
01:16:58,786 --> 01:17:01,366
- How about an internet cafe?
- What about it?

1340
01:17:01,366 --> 01:17:02,576
It's not here.

1341
01:17:02,576 --> 01:17:05,366
There are no games.

1342
01:17:05,366 --> 01:17:09,046
What do you like? Let's take a look.

1343
01:17:09,046 --> 01:17:10,686
What do you want?

1344
01:17:10,686 --> 01:17:12,386
- This one is an easy game.
- These two?

1345
01:17:12,386 --> 01:17:14,766
One of the crowns, or this one.

1346
01:17:15,736 --> 01:17:17,926
Opening. One, two, three!

1347
01:17:19,756 --> 01:17:22,156
[Wins one of So Yun's picks]

1348
01:17:22,156 --> 01:17:24,466
- I got it.
- You actually got it!

1349
01:17:24,466 --> 01:17:26,486
She sincerely loves it.

1350
01:17:27,266 --> 01:17:28,736
I love that.

1351
01:17:28,736 --> 01:17:32,236
[Seo Won and So Yun have similar tastes]

1352
01:17:32,236 --> 01:17:34,856
- We have similar tastes.
- Really?

1353
01:17:34,856 --> 01:17:38,856
- These places make you want...
- To stay forever.

1354
01:17:38,856 --> 01:17:40,856
One, two, three!

1355
01:17:41,836 --> 01:17:43,356
It's a sleepy eye!

1356
01:17:43,356 --> 01:17:47,146
- It's so cute.
- I'm happy with any of these.

1357
01:17:47,146 --> 01:17:49,086
[Focuses]

1358
01:17:50,646 --> 01:17:51,946
Go for it.

1359
01:17:51,946 --> 01:17:53,646
[Earnest]

1360
01:17:54,886 --> 01:17:57,026
- Right here?
- Hold on.

1361
01:17:58,086 --> 01:17:59,746
- Forward?
- This way.

1362
01:17:59,746 --> 01:18:01,136
Oh, my gosh!

1363
01:18:01,136 --> 01:18:03,436
[They work together to win a doll]

1364
01:18:04,996 --> 01:18:07,546
Please!

1365
01:18:08,396 --> 01:18:10,606
They got it!

1366
01:18:10,606 --> 01:18:12,136
Awesome!

1367
01:18:12,976 --> 01:18:17,356
- These memories last.
- Gosh. Thank you so much.

1368
01:18:17,356 --> 01:18:20,006
- I'm tired.
- I'll never forget this.

1369
01:18:20,736 --> 01:18:24,976
[The two arrive at the second location]

1370
01:18:24,976 --> 01:18:28,656
- It's adorable here.
- It's cozy and cute.

1371
01:18:32,016 --> 01:18:34,766
I bet the cheese arrangement will be pretty.

1372
01:18:34,766 --> 01:18:37,176
- Yeah.
- Don't spoil it for me.

1373
01:18:37,176 --> 01:18:39,606
As someone who values
a fully immersive experience.

1374
01:18:39,606 --> 01:18:42,256
- So Yun must know this place.
- Our event planner.

1375
01:18:43,626 --> 01:18:46,806
Those are all actual routines of mine.

1376
01:18:46,806 --> 01:18:48,926
I really bring home the flowers
after my shoot.

1377
01:18:48,926 --> 01:18:51,726
Right. He's like that.

1378
01:18:51,726 --> 01:18:55,836
Do you plan a lot of surprises
for your girlfriend?

1379
01:18:57,236 --> 01:18:58,906
I do.

1380
01:18:59,726 --> 01:19:01,526
I like gifting flowers.

1381
01:19:01,526 --> 01:19:04,256
I gift mostly flowers and letters.

1382
01:19:04,256 --> 01:19:06,866
- Gosh.
- That's so nice.

1383
01:19:08,166 --> 01:19:10,716
You gift what's difficult for most men.

1384
01:19:10,716 --> 01:19:12,796
- That's right.
- Right.

1385
01:19:12,796 --> 01:19:14,856
Gifts are no big deal.

1386
01:19:14,856 --> 01:19:18,596
I give gifts whenever it crosses my mind.

1387
01:19:23,866 --> 01:19:26,596
I'm having so many great experiences today.

1388
01:19:27,646 --> 01:19:30,376
You'll have more from now on.

1389
01:19:30,376 --> 01:19:31,936
Sounds good.

1390
01:19:33,986 --> 01:19:35,736
So Yun has been revived!

1391
01:19:35,736 --> 01:19:39,436
So Yun has fallen for Seo Won's charm.

1392
01:19:41,556 --> 01:19:42,396
[Wow!]

1393
01:19:44,456 --> 01:19:48,006
This is an icing cookie, and this
is a Basque cheesecake.

1394
01:19:48,836 --> 01:19:51,846
This is so cute. This is unbelievable.

1395
01:19:51,846 --> 01:19:54,396
As someone who enjoys event planning...

1396
01:19:54,396 --> 01:19:56,516
I think I'm going to cry.

1397
01:19:57,486 --> 01:20:00,266
How did you find this place?

1398
01:20:00,906 --> 01:20:05,216
I feel like I've received a precious gift.

1399
01:20:06,456 --> 01:20:08,346
It looks like it's your birthday.

1400
01:20:09,346 --> 01:20:11,026
Looking nice.

1401
01:20:11,026 --> 01:20:15,676
Seo Won probably realizes that
So Yun is referring to him, right?

1402
01:20:15,676 --> 01:20:17,516
I don't think so.

1403
01:20:17,516 --> 01:20:19,886
- Am I in it?
- You look like girlfriend material.

1404
01:20:22,896 --> 01:20:24,646
This looks like your cake.

1405
01:20:25,686 --> 01:20:29,336
- You're the one who prepared it.
- I did.

1406
01:20:29,336 --> 01:20:30,956
I-I did.

1407
01:20:32,386 --> 01:20:33,666
Blow out the candle.

1408
01:20:33,666 --> 01:20:34,896
- No.
- Why not?

1409
01:20:34,896 --> 01:20:37,066
Let's enjoy it more. It's too beautiful.

1410
01:20:37,066 --> 01:20:40,236
Gosh, he wants to enjoy it more.

1411
01:20:40,236 --> 01:20:42,476
Gosh, seriously.

1412
01:20:43,176 --> 01:20:44,126
It's so pretty.

1413
01:20:44,126 --> 01:20:46,646
Gosh, she's the pretty one.

1414
01:20:47,406 --> 01:20:48,576
Do you want this?

1415
01:20:48,576 --> 01:20:50,316
- What?
- The cupid.

1416
01:20:50,316 --> 01:20:52,056
Cupid's arrow.

1417
01:20:52,756 --> 01:20:55,106
- I want it.
- You can eat it.

1418
01:20:55,106 --> 01:20:57,216
Aim well on the last day.

1419
01:21:00,396 --> 01:21:01,276
[Shoot]

1420
01:21:01,916 --> 01:21:04,386
Oh, this one is- That's hot.

1421
01:21:13,866 --> 01:21:15,236
It's called...

1422
01:21:15,236 --> 01:21:17,636
- Basque cheesecake.
- Oh, you know.

1423
01:21:17,636 --> 01:21:18,886
[Nom]

1424
01:21:18,886 --> 01:21:19,936
It's my favorite.

1425
01:21:19,936 --> 01:21:21,496
[Flustered]

1426
01:21:25,706 --> 01:21:27,996
Why did you tell me after I ate it?

1427
01:21:28,656 --> 01:21:30,626
I'll buy you one next time.

1428
01:21:30,626 --> 01:21:33,116
I bet he'll really buy one next time.

1429
01:21:41,406 --> 01:21:43,366
What?

1430
01:21:43,366 --> 01:21:45,226
Do I look funny?

1431
01:21:45,226 --> 01:21:46,566
A little.

1432
01:21:48,416 --> 01:21:50,376
You do look funny.

1433
01:21:51,086 --> 01:21:52,996
Hit-or-miss?

1434
01:21:56,496 --> 01:21:58,066
Chipping away at my confidence.

1435
01:21:58,066 --> 01:21:59,646
[A smile blooms across So Yun's face]

1436
01:21:59,646 --> 01:22:02,536
- I thought you would boost it.
- I'm joking.

1437
01:22:04,026 --> 01:22:07,676
- She totally fell for him!
- I agree.

1438
01:22:07,676 --> 01:22:10,406
- She fell for him.
- Honestly, how could she not?

1439
01:22:10,406 --> 01:22:13,216
If you fall for someone
who wasn't even on your radar,

1440
01:22:13,216 --> 01:22:14,766
it hits you harder.

1441
01:22:14,766 --> 01:22:17,046
I don't think she realized his charm.

1442
01:22:17,046 --> 01:22:21,016
Once you come to a realization,
you're hopeless.

1443
01:22:22,316 --> 01:22:24,366
How can it be this good? It's so good.

1444
01:22:24,366 --> 01:22:27,886
This aftertaste is a first for me.

1445
01:22:32,156 --> 01:22:34,446
I'm glad we made plans today.

1446
01:22:34,446 --> 01:22:36,826
- Why?
- It's fun.

1447
01:22:38,896 --> 01:22:40,686
It's memorable.

1448
01:22:42,886 --> 01:22:44,216
Yeah.

1449
01:22:47,566 --> 01:22:50,806
- I think she fell for him.
- So Yun, tell him.

1450
01:22:52,276 --> 01:22:54,166
This is hard.

1451
01:22:54,166 --> 01:22:56,546
Dealing with your feelings?

1452
01:22:57,576 --> 01:22:59,112
- Your heart is heavy?
- Yeah.

1453
01:22:59,112 --> 01:23:00,139
Oh, no.

1454
01:23:00,139 --> 01:23:02,623
I think it's harder because she fell for him.

1455
01:23:06,496 --> 01:23:08,786
But can...

1456
01:23:08,786 --> 01:23:11,266
Can you tell what I'm thinking?

1457
01:23:11,266 --> 01:23:13,493
No. I can't see anything.

1458
01:23:13,493 --> 01:23:16,186
He's so perceptive, but oblivious to So Yun.

1459
01:23:16,186 --> 01:23:17,863
Why not?

1460
01:23:19,726 --> 01:23:23,946
- I don't know.
- He's oblivious when it comes to himself.

1461
01:23:24,756 --> 01:23:27,736
- Keep charging. You're good at that.
- That's not it!

1462
01:23:27,736 --> 01:23:30,786
She's charging right at you!

1463
01:23:31,826 --> 01:23:33,886
This is so frustrating.

1464
01:23:33,886 --> 01:23:35,016
What time is it?

1465
01:23:35,016 --> 01:23:37,256
12:30 a.m., so it'll be 1:00 a.m.
when we return.

1466
01:23:37,256 --> 01:23:38,356
1:00 a.m.?

1467
01:23:38,356 --> 01:23:41,016
- You didn't have to wait today.
- Yeah.

1468
01:23:41,016 --> 01:23:43,166
- Are you happy?
- Yeah.

1469
01:23:46,106 --> 01:23:48,466
You're always waiting.

1470
01:23:50,456 --> 01:23:52,406
Don't stay out so late.

1471
01:23:52,406 --> 01:23:55,176
- He doesn't get that?
- Seriously.

1472
01:23:55,176 --> 01:23:57,316
I do go home early.

1473
01:24:02,976 --> 01:24:05,586
What a great meal.

1474
01:24:10,316 --> 01:24:12,866
[What just happened?]

1475
01:24:12,866 --> 01:24:15,906
He's oblivious when it comes to himself.

1476
01:24:15,906 --> 01:24:18,606
But I think So Yun has found her path.

1477
01:24:18,606 --> 01:24:21,196
It's funny how Seo Won has no idea.

1478
01:24:21,196 --> 01:24:24,446
- Is it an act? Wasn't she being obvious?
- It could be an act.

1479
01:24:24,446 --> 01:24:28,866
Men like him usually are oblivious
when it comes to themselves.

1480
01:24:28,866 --> 01:24:30,896
- You think he knows or not?
- I bet he knows.

1481
01:24:30,896 --> 01:24:32,686
- I don't think he does.
- He doesn't.

1482
01:24:32,686 --> 01:24:35,936
Because So Yun never told him outright
when Seo Won asked

1483
01:24:35,936 --> 01:24:37,956
how her date went yesterday.

1484
01:24:37,956 --> 01:24:39,966
- She said it went well.
- That's right.

1485
01:24:39,966 --> 01:24:42,566
He thinks it's going well
with her and Wu Yeol.

1486
01:24:42,566 --> 01:24:46,216
He's aware that her feelings
for Wu Yeol were deep.

1487
01:24:46,216 --> 01:24:47,806
She never said she gave up.

1488
01:24:47,806 --> 01:24:51,246
He didn't reject her,
but he just turned a blind eye?

1489
01:24:51,246 --> 01:24:53,316
No, no. He has no idea.

1490
01:24:53,316 --> 01:24:56,036
Well, I can read Seo Won's expressions.

1491
01:24:56,036 --> 01:24:58,676
- He doesn't know at this point.
- He has no idea.

1492
01:24:58,676 --> 01:25:03,266
She said her date with Wu Yeol went well,

1493
01:25:03,266 --> 01:25:06,556
so he's just supporting her
to pursue Wu Yeol.

1494
01:25:06,556 --> 01:25:09,816
That's the extent of his feelings.

1495
01:25:09,816 --> 01:25:14,346
Seo Won is not the type to
turn a blind eye to her feelings.

1496
01:25:14,346 --> 01:25:20,246
So Yun also said she's having a hard time.

1497
01:25:20,246 --> 01:25:24,236
Struggling with coming to terms
with her growing feelings for him.

1498
01:25:24,236 --> 01:25:26,146
- Right.
- Oh, no.

1499
01:25:26,146 --> 01:25:28,376
It's hard to have feelings for someone.

1500
01:25:28,376 --> 01:25:30,496
It drains a lot of energy.

1501
01:25:30,496 --> 01:25:33,156
So Yun always had to watch

1502
01:25:33,156 --> 01:25:35,826
the man she liked have feelings
for another woman.

1503
01:25:35,826 --> 01:25:37,556
- Exactly.
- That's why she's struggling.

1504
01:25:37,556 --> 01:25:40,186
And she knows how much he likes Gyu Ri.

1505
01:25:40,186 --> 01:25:41,936
That's why her heart is heavy.

1506
01:25:41,936 --> 01:25:44,006
It must pain her.

1507
01:25:44,006 --> 01:25:46,756
Everyone is in pain!

1508
01:25:49,166 --> 01:25:53,706
[Waiting for someone after work]

1509
01:25:54,216 --> 01:25:59,626
[Gyu Ri and Wu Yeol's nickname date]

1510
01:26:03,226 --> 01:26:07,766
Didn't you have a drink yesterday?

1511
01:26:07,766 --> 01:26:10,266
- Soju?
- Yeah. Half a bottle.

1512
01:26:24,486 --> 01:26:26,066
This looks good.

1513
01:26:26,066 --> 01:26:27,576
I know.

1514
01:26:28,356 --> 01:26:31,376
- It's been so long since I had this.
- Me, too.

1515
01:26:32,236 --> 01:26:34,396
Shall we have a shot?

1516
01:26:34,396 --> 01:26:36,086
Cheers.

1517
01:26:45,426 --> 01:26:47,146
Thank you.

1518
01:26:47,816 --> 01:26:49,786
I'll hold the glass.

1519
01:26:58,826 --> 01:27:03,056
So that pop-up you spoke about last time.

1520
01:27:05,036 --> 01:27:07,296
It's being pushed back.

1521
01:27:07,296 --> 01:27:10,876
We've partnered with a department store
for an upcoming pop-up.

1522
01:27:10,876 --> 01:27:12,566
- Inside the department store?
- Yes.

1523
01:27:12,566 --> 01:27:15,506
I'm going to be dead next week.

1524
01:27:15,506 --> 01:27:18,126
I might work overtime.

1525
01:27:20,516 --> 01:27:22,876
I don't know why.

1526
01:27:22,876 --> 01:27:25,096
I wonder if it's the location.

1527
01:27:28,996 --> 01:27:30,786
I'll go.

1528
01:27:31,686 --> 01:27:32,996
Sure.

1529
01:27:35,166 --> 01:27:37,196
It sounds fun.

1530
01:27:37,196 --> 01:27:38,226
[Smiles]

1531
01:27:38,896 --> 01:27:42,836
It'll feel a bit different seeing you there.

1532
01:27:42,836 --> 01:27:44,356
Yeah.

1533
01:27:48,706 --> 01:27:50,646
[Glances]

1534
01:27:51,896 --> 01:27:57,066
Don't you think it'll be awkward

1535
01:27:57,066 --> 01:28:00,706
if we end up exchanging numbers
and stay in touch?

1536
01:28:00,706 --> 01:28:03,956
Have you thought about it?

1537
01:28:05,096 --> 01:28:06,256
[Nods]

1538
01:28:06,256 --> 01:28:10,556
I have. I thought
about a potential group chat.

1539
01:28:10,556 --> 01:28:12,606
- Group chat?
- Yeah.

1540
01:28:12,606 --> 01:28:17,846
[Imagining our future selves]

1541
01:28:17,846 --> 01:28:21,176
I think neither of us will participate.

1542
01:28:21,176 --> 01:28:23,836
- Oh, really? I think I will.
- Really?

1543
01:28:26,586 --> 01:28:29,256
I take part in lively things like that.

1544
01:28:30,026 --> 01:28:32,546
Lively group chats?

1545
01:28:37,436 --> 01:28:39,586
Back then...

1546
01:28:39,586 --> 01:28:42,806
wasn't our time at the beach
a bit disappointing?

1547
01:28:42,806 --> 01:28:48,196
[Cautiously brings up that day]

1548
01:28:48,856 --> 01:28:51,136
[Thinks hard]

1549
01:28:56,036 --> 01:29:01,646
It wasn't disappointing, actually. Because...

1550
01:29:01,646 --> 01:29:04,556
- we went to the cafe, too.
- That's right.

1551
01:29:05,276 --> 01:29:08,546
We were sitting pretty close. That was nice.

1552
01:29:08,546 --> 01:29:09,896
He's being honest.

1553
01:29:09,896 --> 01:29:12,006
[Nods]

1554
01:29:13,916 --> 01:29:18,436
[The conversation pauses]

1555
01:29:20,556 --> 01:29:25,986
I think everyone was still awkward
with each other at that time.

1556
01:29:25,986 --> 01:29:29,486
Jun Hyeon didn't talk to me at all

1557
01:29:29,486 --> 01:29:32,096
even though he sat right across from me.

1558
01:29:33,211 --> 01:29:34,018
Yeah.

1559
01:29:34,018 --> 01:29:38,566
You and Yu Gyeong weren't
exactly chatting each other up, either.

1560
01:29:38,566 --> 01:29:40,786
There was some distance between us.

1561
01:29:43,816 --> 01:29:45,656
What kind?

1562
01:29:47,856 --> 01:29:50,996
But I think...

1563
01:29:52,626 --> 01:29:56,636
we've grown more comfortable.

1564
01:29:56,636 --> 01:29:59,486
We've grown closer to each other.

1565
01:29:59,486 --> 01:30:01,816
Look at her expression!

1566
01:30:03,106 --> 01:30:04,586
You're right.

1567
01:30:06,886 --> 01:30:11,866
[The change finally sinks in]

1568
01:30:12,536 --> 01:30:18,026
[and silence falls between them]

1569
01:30:23,946 --> 01:30:26,396
[Glances]

1570
01:30:32,896 --> 01:30:35,276
Yesterday,

1571
01:30:35,276 --> 01:30:39,036
you said you change
depending on who you're with.

1572
01:30:39,036 --> 01:30:40,906
She's dwelling on what he said.

1573
01:30:42,106 --> 01:30:45,186
[Thinks hard]

1574
01:30:49,196 --> 01:30:51,716
He looks tired today.

1575
01:30:53,366 --> 01:30:56,076
What did you mean?

1576
01:30:57,106 --> 01:31:01,986
When you said you start acting cutesy?

1577
01:31:02,866 --> 01:31:05,466
Have you shown that side
in front of everyone?

1578
01:31:05,466 --> 01:31:07,696
Not in front of everyone.

1579
01:31:08,456 --> 01:31:10,506
- It's intriguing.
- Are you curious?

1580
01:31:11,206 --> 01:31:14,246
I don't think you want to know. Do you?

1581
01:31:14,246 --> 01:31:18,446
People either love it or hate it.
I don't think you want to know.

1582
01:31:23,316 --> 01:31:26,836
That side of me appears

1583
01:31:26,836 --> 01:31:30,466
depending on who I'm with,
without even realizing.

1584
01:31:34,116 --> 01:31:36,016
Then...

1585
01:31:39,706 --> 01:31:43,896
if you could return to that first day,

1586
01:31:47,286 --> 01:31:50,186
is there something you want to change?

1587
01:31:50,186 --> 01:31:52,296
Her curiosity makes sense.

1588
01:31:56,176 --> 01:31:58,786
When you think about it,

1589
01:31:58,786 --> 01:32:01,346
these moments right now only exist

1590
01:32:01,346 --> 01:32:03,936
because of those past moments.

1591
01:32:06,826 --> 01:32:08,536
I'm content.

1592
01:32:11,046 --> 01:32:13,546
You're right. That's true.

1593
01:32:20,946 --> 01:32:26,866
But honestly, even if we had met up
a bunch of times in the beginning,

1594
01:32:26,866 --> 01:32:31,456
I think things would've turned out
the exact same way for the first week.

1595
01:32:31,456 --> 01:32:37,026
In the beginning part of a relationship,

1596
01:32:37,026 --> 01:32:40,196
I don't really open up to them.

1597
01:32:41,396 --> 01:32:45,416
That's also why it's hard for me
to speak casually.

1598
01:32:46,176 --> 01:32:50,666
Well, I'm not being guarded.

1599
01:32:50,666 --> 01:32:52,796
Actually, maybe I am.

1600
01:32:52,796 --> 01:32:56,656
But I just don't want to get
disappointed or get hurt later on.

1601
01:32:58,726 --> 01:33:03,236
- I would change this if I could go back.
- What?

1602
01:33:03,236 --> 01:33:06,236
It would've been nice to listen
to music on the way.

1603
01:33:06,236 --> 01:33:07,966
A playlist.

1604
01:33:08,966 --> 01:33:12,836
I think our playlists would be similar.

1605
01:33:16,196 --> 01:33:16,976
[Nods]

1606
01:33:16,976 --> 01:33:19,226
He doesn't know what to say.

1607
01:33:22,566 --> 01:33:30,036
[Gaps in the conversation
that aren't easily filled]

1608
01:33:31,636 --> 01:33:33,466
[Glances]

1609
01:33:35,796 --> 01:33:39,146
Last shot? Or do you want to drink more?

1610
01:33:39,146 --> 01:33:40,716
No, I'm good right now.

1611
01:33:40,716 --> 01:33:43,156
Well, we can move on.

1612
01:33:43,896 --> 01:33:47,226
[They head to the next location]

1613
01:33:47,226 --> 01:33:50,876
[A bar in Gwangjin-gu]

1614
01:33:59,026 --> 01:34:01,206
Let's talk about our nicknames.

1615
01:34:02,026 --> 01:34:03,546
Oh, today?

1616
01:34:03,546 --> 01:34:06,606
I had a feeling
we'd talk about this if we met.

1617
01:34:06,606 --> 01:34:08,226
Yeah.

1618
01:34:08,226 --> 01:34:12,886
When did you learn everyone's?

1619
01:34:12,886 --> 01:34:17,056
I actually learned yours on the second day.

1620
01:34:17,056 --> 01:34:18,376
Me?

1621
01:34:19,136 --> 01:34:22,156
- How? It was obvious?
- As soon as I saw it, I realized.

1622
01:34:22,156 --> 01:34:25,086
"Oh, Sweet Potato"?

1623
01:34:25,936 --> 01:34:28,726
I think I wrote, "Thanks to you,"
or something like that.

1624
01:34:28,726 --> 01:34:31,006
Yeah, you did.

1625
01:34:31,676 --> 01:34:35,076
That was our first contact, right?

1626
01:34:37,826 --> 01:34:42,146
[Silence instead of an answer]

1627
01:34:45,416 --> 01:34:48,896
How would you feel
if the messages stopped coming?

1628
01:34:50,826 --> 01:34:55,426
I would feel bothered, of course.
I'm only human, so it bothered me.

1629
01:35:01,956 --> 01:35:04,086
Go on.

1630
01:35:04,086 --> 01:35:06,936
It bothered me. But...

1631
01:35:10,166 --> 01:35:15,516
I was dwelling on it in the beginning.

1632
01:35:15,516 --> 01:35:17,406
But now...

1633
01:35:20,456 --> 01:35:24,046
Now, it doesn't concern me at all.

1634
01:35:24,746 --> 01:35:26,306
I just...

1635
01:35:27,876 --> 01:35:30,156
think my feelings are more important.

1636
01:35:31,076 --> 01:35:35,246
[My feelings are more important
than the texts]

1637
01:35:50,816 --> 01:35:52,516
That's how I felt.

1638
01:35:53,706 --> 01:35:55,996
That's how you felt.

1639
01:35:55,996 --> 01:35:59,176
But my mindset has completely changed now.

1640
01:36:00,646 --> 01:36:05,286
[His standards for love have changed]

1641
01:36:06,496 --> 01:36:09,286
- I'll get some more napkins.
- Will you?

1642
01:36:14,706 --> 01:36:16,466
[Nods]

1643
01:36:19,866 --> 01:36:24,036
But weren't you ever worried
that looking way too close

1644
01:36:24,036 --> 01:36:28,246
to just one person might push others away?

1645
01:36:28,246 --> 01:36:32,446
Didn't you think it might stop someone
else from approaching you?

1646
01:36:34,846 --> 01:36:36,276
I did.

1647
01:36:36,276 --> 01:36:37,566
Of course, I did.

1648
01:36:37,566 --> 01:36:41,276
It's a shared living space, so it's
impossible not to be mindful.

1649
01:36:43,156 --> 01:36:44,836
Looking back,

1650
01:36:47,606 --> 01:36:51,546
I didn't act out of bounds even though
I had those thoughts.

1651
01:36:57,626 --> 01:37:00,146
We mustered up the courage, nevertheless.

1652
01:37:00,146 --> 01:37:02,196
[Nods]

1653
01:37:02,196 --> 01:37:04,686
But I think I made the right choice.

1654
01:37:07,756 --> 01:37:10,316
We can't tell the future.

1655
01:37:12,326 --> 01:37:16,656
Honestly, I acted like
I didn't have feelings.

1656
01:37:16,656 --> 01:37:19,576
It took time for me to come to terms with it.

1657
01:37:19,576 --> 01:37:22,216
I tried my best not to seem that way.

1658
01:37:23,026 --> 01:37:29,376
[Wu Yeol chose courage instead of regret]

1659
01:37:31,476 --> 01:37:38,546
[Wu Yeol cautiously relays his true feelings]

1660
01:37:38,546 --> 01:37:39,986
So dry.

1661
01:37:39,986 --> 01:37:42,206
Wu Yeol is being sincere.

1662
01:37:42,206 --> 01:37:45,246
[Yu Gyeong and Seong Min return home]

1663
01:37:45,246 --> 01:37:47,006
- What?
- No one's home.

1664
01:37:47,006 --> 01:37:49,576
I guess that's possible.

1665
01:37:49,576 --> 01:37:52,316
Looking at the number of slippers,

1666
01:37:52,316 --> 01:37:54,516
I don't think anyone is home.

1667
01:37:56,196 --> 01:37:58,946
[They set up drinks on the first floor]

1668
01:37:58,946 --> 01:38:02,516
It's been so long. It might be rusty.

1669
01:38:02,516 --> 01:38:04,466
What's with the guitar?

1670
01:38:04,466 --> 01:38:07,286
What's this? Did he save that
as his secret weapon?

1671
01:38:07,286 --> 01:38:10,376
He's holding a secret concert just for her.

1672
01:38:10,376 --> 01:38:13,216
[Curious]

1673
01:38:13,216 --> 01:38:14,326
[Cracks up]

1674
01:38:14,326 --> 01:38:17,616
Hold on. This is so out of tune.

1675
01:38:17,616 --> 01:38:19,936
You have to tune it?

1676
01:38:20,636 --> 01:38:22,006
I do.

1677
01:38:22,616 --> 01:38:25,296
You're hilarious.

1678
01:38:26,006 --> 01:38:28,156
They're alone, and he's playing for her...

1679
01:38:28,156 --> 01:38:30,516
[Click]

1680
01:38:30,516 --> 01:38:32,546
I play while watching YouTube.
Since I don't really know how.

1681
01:38:32,546 --> 01:38:36,026
- For the chords?
- Yeah. I look at it.

1682
01:38:39,606 --> 01:38:45,066
[Cautiously begins playing]

1683
01:38:46,676 --> 01:38:48,126
I'm shy.

1684
01:38:49,986 --> 01:38:53,236
[Yu Gyeong sings along]

1685
01:38:54,436 --> 01:38:56,236
They're singing together?

1686
01:39:02,896 --> 01:39:03,926
They sound nice.

1687
01:39:03,926 --> 01:39:08,246
[Stares]

1688
01:39:09,806 --> 01:39:11,376
They look lovely.

1689
01:39:11,376 --> 01:39:13,216
I had this picture in my mind.

1690
01:39:13,216 --> 01:39:15,156
Where I'm killing it.

1691
01:39:15,156 --> 01:39:17,006
The tuning is off.

1692
01:39:17,666 --> 01:39:18,986
- Are you sure?
- It's been so long.

1693
01:39:18,986 --> 01:39:21,076
I told you I wasn't good.

1694
01:39:21,076 --> 01:39:22,796
I'm just setting the mood.

1695
01:39:22,796 --> 01:39:26,386
But you're able to play
after reading the chords.

1696
01:39:26,386 --> 01:39:28,326
I can play if I read the chords.

1697
01:39:28,326 --> 01:39:30,436
You know how to play, then.

1698
01:39:35,266 --> 01:39:37,816
Seong Min really likes Yu Gyeong.

1699
01:39:39,406 --> 01:39:42,536
[Tries again, encouraged by her support]

1700
01:39:44,086 --> 01:39:45,826
You're good!

1701
01:39:47,076 --> 01:39:50,816
[Playing hard]

1702
01:40:02,276 --> 01:40:06,246
[What type of emotion
is he trying to deliver?]

1703
01:40:14,996 --> 01:40:17,586
Whoa, you're good at this song!

1704
01:40:17,586 --> 01:40:20,096
[Excited]

1705
01:40:20,096 --> 01:40:21,586
It's quite delightful.

1706
01:40:21,586 --> 01:40:23,216
Where are you going?

1707
01:40:34,276 --> 01:40:37,746
By chance, are you a hypocritical person?

1708
01:40:40,786 --> 01:40:44,076
I think being honest is good and

1709
01:40:44,076 --> 01:40:47,076
I think I'm an honest person.

1710
01:40:47,076 --> 01:40:48,596
But...

1711
01:40:50,126 --> 01:40:54,416
I do have feelings I want to hide.

1712
01:40:54,416 --> 01:40:56,206
I'm conflicted.

1713
01:40:56,206 --> 01:40:59,276
Yu Gyeong's heart lies elsewhere right now.

1714
01:40:59,276 --> 01:41:01,156
[Nods]

1715
01:41:03,396 --> 01:41:10,276
[Seong Min leaves the guitar in the kitchen]

1716
01:41:14,196 --> 01:41:15,796
- What's this?
- Hi!

1717
01:41:15,796 --> 01:41:16,996
[Min Ju and Jun Hyeon return just then]

1718
01:41:16,996 --> 01:41:19,226
You guys are in big trouble!

1719
01:41:19,226 --> 01:41:21,176
What the heck are you doing?

1720
01:41:21,176 --> 01:41:23,196
What the heck are we doing? Waiting!

1721
01:41:23,196 --> 01:41:24,846
What time is it now?

1722
01:41:24,846 --> 01:41:25,946
Listen to me.

1723
01:41:25,946 --> 01:41:29,566
I worked overtime and
came home at 10:30 p.m.

1724
01:41:29,566 --> 01:41:31,446
But no one was home.

1725
01:41:31,446 --> 01:41:33,336
[Glances]

1726
01:41:33,336 --> 01:41:35,456
- Everyone went on a date!
- Exactly!

1727
01:41:35,456 --> 01:41:37,066
Oh, no.

1728
01:41:37,066 --> 01:41:39,226
Only Min Ju was home.

1729
01:41:39,226 --> 01:41:40,406
You were home?

1730
01:41:40,406 --> 01:41:42,406
And was it around 8:00 p.m.?

1731
01:41:42,406 --> 01:41:44,916
I've been grilling meat and
eating alone since 8:00 p.m.

1732
01:41:44,916 --> 01:41:46,586
[Pouts]

1733
01:41:46,586 --> 01:41:49,216
I ate dinner alone.

1734
01:41:49,216 --> 01:41:51,406
What did you guys do?

1735
01:41:51,406 --> 01:41:53,446
Seriously, what the heck?

1736
01:41:53,446 --> 01:41:56,286
Is it a secret?

1737
01:41:57,286 --> 01:41:59,986
Or you just don't want to say?

1738
01:41:59,986 --> 01:42:01,506
What did you do?

1739
01:42:01,506 --> 01:42:03,836
Where did you go?

1740
01:42:03,836 --> 01:42:06,386
Can't you just tell us? We'll tell you, too.

1741
01:42:06,386 --> 01:42:08,116
It's weird of them not to say.

1742
01:42:08,116 --> 01:42:09,816
We met at home.

1743
01:42:09,816 --> 01:42:13,676
Geez, so cliché.

1744
01:42:15,076 --> 01:42:16,496
That's funny.

1745
01:42:16,496 --> 01:42:19,536
He played the guitar and sang for her.

1746
01:42:21,016 --> 01:42:24,916
[Jun Hyeon goes upstairs]

1747
01:42:25,436 --> 01:42:27,236
Did you eat anything good?

1748
01:42:28,026 --> 01:42:30,166
We had hamburgers.

1749
01:42:32,646 --> 01:42:35,026
I think Min Ju caught on.

1750
01:42:36,256 --> 01:42:38,506
[Glances]

1751
01:42:38,506 --> 01:42:41,836
[The guitar Seong Min left]

1752
01:42:42,646 --> 01:42:44,616
She saw the guitar just now.

1753
01:42:44,616 --> 01:42:47,556
She caught on that he sang for her?

1754
01:42:49,116 --> 01:42:51,946
I sometimes feel like playing the guitar.

1755
01:42:51,946 --> 01:42:54,696
Bring it and show off upstairs.

1756
01:42:54,696 --> 01:42:56,186
Sing a song.

1757
01:42:56,186 --> 01:42:58,036
You need to play up your strengths.

1758
01:42:58,036 --> 01:43:00,486
[Min Ju looked forward to
Seong Min playing the guitar]

1759
01:43:00,486 --> 01:43:02,446
[Min Ju really looked forward to it]

1760
01:43:03,576 --> 01:43:05,876
I'm losing it.

1761
01:43:05,876 --> 01:43:10,046
[Min Ju's heart is breaking]

1762
01:43:13,366 --> 01:43:14,966
[Turns away]

1763
01:43:31,226 --> 01:43:35,256
She should've told her what she
talked about with Seong Min.

1764
01:43:36,256 --> 01:43:38,766
You look like a total madam right now.

1765
01:43:38,766 --> 01:43:42,456
- I'm wearing tweed.
- Come on!

1766
01:43:42,456 --> 01:43:44,096
Go and get changed.

1767
01:43:44,096 --> 01:43:46,306
The disparity between us
is too big. Look at me.

1768
01:43:46,306 --> 01:43:48,286
I can only wear this once,

1769
01:43:48,286 --> 01:43:50,616
so I want to show everyone before changing.

1770
01:43:50,616 --> 01:43:53,046
- It's really pretty, though.
- She must want to show Wu Yeol.

1771
01:43:53,046 --> 01:43:54,896
It goes well with your pants.

1772
01:43:54,896 --> 01:43:57,336
- These are my pants.
- I thought so.

1773
01:43:57,336 --> 01:44:00,486
Wait, so who's exactly outside?

1774
01:44:00,486 --> 01:44:03,256
- Who went out with who?
- I don't know.

1775
01:44:03,256 --> 01:44:05,116
My guess...

1776
01:44:06,856 --> 01:44:09,006
is Gyu Ri and Wu Yeol.

1777
01:44:10,176 --> 01:44:13,946
- Since Wu Yeol went out with
- They're heartbroken today.

1778
01:44:13,946 --> 01:44:16,336
So Yun yesterday.

1779
01:44:17,846 --> 01:44:19,556
I can apply eye drops now, Yu Gyeong.

1780
01:44:19,556 --> 01:44:21,376
- Really?
- With no hesitation.

1781
01:44:21,376 --> 01:44:22,866
You've improved since then.

1782
01:44:22,866 --> 01:44:24,316
Doesn't this smell the best?

1783
01:44:24,316 --> 01:44:27,281
I don't know,
but Wu Yeol said he likes this one.

1784
01:44:27,281 --> 01:44:28,986
Oh, my!

1785
01:44:30,596 --> 01:44:33,356
Don't your hands feel so dry here?

1786
01:44:33,356 --> 01:44:35,026
Right? I agree.

1787
01:44:35,706 --> 01:44:38,686
I have some lotion on right now.
The hot pink one.

1788
01:44:38,686 --> 01:44:39,876
Let me smell.

1789
01:44:41,476 --> 01:44:43,616
- No wonder.
- You like it?

1790
01:44:43,616 --> 01:44:46,526
- I like it.
- He keeps giving her butterflies.

1791
01:44:46,526 --> 01:44:49,456
I'm applying everything you like.

1792
01:44:49,456 --> 01:44:51,736
Wu Yeol is all she can think about.

1793
01:44:51,736 --> 01:44:53,636
What perfume do you use?

1794
01:44:53,636 --> 01:44:55,806
From the perfume...

1795
01:44:56,546 --> 01:44:58,726
to hand cream...

1796
01:44:58,726 --> 01:45:00,466
Daebak.

1797
01:45:00,466 --> 01:45:01,986
I have my own problems, but so do you.

1798
01:45:01,986 --> 01:45:03,916
